title: torah_(object)
body:
The Torah (תּוֹרָה) is the compilation of the first five books of the Hebrew Bible, and together with the Talmud form the foundational works of [[Judaism]]. It is also considered part of holy works in [[Christianity]] (the Old Testament) and [[Islam]] (توراة‎). 

It is usually depicted as a double-handled scroll, as would be kept in and read from at the [[synagogue]], however normal book versions are also common.

title: st._louis_(azur_lane)
body:
[i]Not to be confused with [[Saint-Louis_(azur_lane)|Saint-Louis]], a personification of the French heavy cruiser featured in the same game[/i].

Personification of the United States Navy light cruiser [i]USS St. Louis (CL-49)[/i] in [[Azur Lane]]. Character design by [[Yunsang]], voiced by [[Hikasa Youko]].

She has [[long hair|long]] [[blue hair]] tied in a [[high_ponytail|high]] [[side ponytail]] with [[sidelocks]], and reddish-[[purple eyes]]. Her outfit is similar to her (half)-sister [[honolulu_(azur_lane)|Honolulu]], wearing a [[double-breasted]] [[white_dress|white]] and [[blue_dress|blue]] [[two-tone dress|two-tone]] [[side-tie dress|side-tie]] [[micro dress]], [[white thighhighs]], [[high heels]], and [[white gloves|white]] [[elbow gloves]]. Her [[rigging]] consists of all five of her real-life 15.2 cm triple mounts, two to her left and three to her right.

Historically, she and her sister [[helena_(azur_lane)|Helena]] differed from the first seven [i]Brooklyn[/i]-class light cruisers in having four 127 mm twin turreted mounts instead of eight 127 mm single open pedestal mounts and having their engines and boilers arranged alternately for increased survival. She served from Pearl Harbor to Okinawa before she was sold off to Brazil in 1951 and renamed [i]Almirante Tamandaré[/i], seeing further service until 1976.

title: saint-louis_(azur_lane)
body:
[[Azur Lane]] character.

Added as part of a collaboration between [[Azur Lane]] and [[World of Warships]], Saint-Louis is based off of a [i]Marine Nationale[/i] heavy cruiser proposal designated "C5". The project was intended to bolster France's cruiser forces after the restrictions of the Washington Naval Treaty had been lifted, succeeding [i][[Algerie (azur lane)|Algeriè]][/i] and similar ships. However, design work was suspended after the Fall of France, and no ships of the class were ever laid down.

She is named after King Louis IX of France, the only French monarch canonized as a saint.

Saint-Louis is portrayed with [[long hair|long]] [[grey hair]], [[red eyes]] and [[large breasts]], dressed in crusader-inspired attire. She holds strong religious ideals, believing herself to be subject to God's will. 

As a reference to the game from which she was taken, Saint-Louis has skills that improve her high-explosive damage and increase her speed for short periods of time.

Not to be confused with [[St. Louis (azur lane)|]].
Voiced by [[Seto Asami]].

title: belfast_(azur_lane)
body:
The personification of the Royal Navy light cruiser HMS [i]Belfast[/i] in [[Azur Lane]]. Character design by [[Kisetsu]], voiced by [[Horie Yui]].

As the current head [[maid]] of the Royal Maid Corps, she is extremely responsible and professional, taking pride in her dedication to perfectionist service, caring for and constantly addressing the [[Commander (Azur Lane)|]] as "Master", while being gentle and friendly towards most people. She has [[long hair|long]] [[white hair]], [[blue eyes]], and [[large breasts]], and her signature [[maid]] outfit features a [[chain]] [[choker]] and a [[low neckline]] that exposes a generous amount of [[cleavage]].

She is [[yuri|shipped]] with [[Enterprise (azur lane)|]] in the official anime. While in story, she succeeds her [i]Town[/i]-class elder sister [[Newcastle (Azur Lane)|]] as the head maid of the Royal Maid Corps.

The real life [i]Belfast[/i] was saved from scrapping by private venture and became a tourist attraction afterwards. She is currently part of the Imperial War Museum, permanently moored on the Thames river, near the Tower Bridge, London, since 1971.

Her [[rigging]] consists of all four of her historical 20.3 cm twin gun mounts on her right side (three on her thigh, one on her right shoulder), [[anti-aircraft gun]]s on her boots, and a seaplane cradle on her thighhigh.

She is notable for her old-fashioned militaristic speech patterns and somewhat aggressive personality. Her sister ship, [[Chikuma (Kancolle)|]], is a notable siscon.

title: kaga_(kancolle)
body:
[[Kantai Collection]]'s personification of the Japanese aircraft carrier [i]Kaga[/i]. Character design by [[shibafu_(glock23)|Shibafu]], voiced by [[Iguchi Yuka]]. 

She has [[long hair|long]] [[brown hair]] in a [[side ponytail]], [[tsurime]] [[brown eyes]], and [[large breasts]]. 

Her default outfit consists of a black [[muneate]] over a [[white kimono]] top and [[blue skirt|blue]] [[pleated skirt]], blue [[tasuki]], brown [[apron]] based on the stern end of her flight deck, with the kana "カ" inscribed on it, [[black thighhighs]], and [[platform footwear]]. Her [[rigging]] is very similar to [[akagi (kancolle)|Akagi's]] (and, by extension, all of Shibafu's carriers') own gear: a traditional [[yumi (bow)|yumi bow]], a [[quiver]] with a replica of the ship's mast, her full flight deck attached as a [[shield]] on her left arm and carrier-like [[geta]]. 

She has a stoic personality. In fan works, she is often paired with [[Akagi (kancolle)|]] or [[Zuikaku (Kancolle)|]]. She is sometimes portrayed as having high body temperature or being warm to the touch, due to the fact that the [i]Kaga[/i] was a converted battleship and was prone to overheating due to poor ventilation.

The historical [i]Kaga[/i] was originally designed as a battleship before being converted into a carrier. She was scuttled after being heavily damaged at the [[Battle of Midway]] in 1942.

title: emperor_of_mankind
body:
One of the most important characters in the [[warhammer_40k|Warhammer 40,000]] universe, the God-Emperor of Mankind is a figure seen as the divine ruler of all humanity. He united a fractured Terra (in ancient times also known as [[earth_(planet)|Earth]]) following the collapse of mankind's previous civilization before setting out on a galaxy-wide campaign (known as the Great Crusade) to reunite lost human worlds and reclaim his demigod sons known as Primarchs.

One, [[horus_lupercal|Horus]], would betray him and rally half the Primarchs to the cause of [[chaos_(warhammer)|Chaos]], triggering a civil war. The Emperor would slay Horus, but was mortally wounded in turn and encased upon a life-support device known as the Golden Throne, where mankind would quickly worship him as a god.

Generally depicted in 2 forms:
* During the Great Crusade, as a very tall human wearing a extremely decorated [[gold armor|golden]]  [[power armor]], a golden [[laurel crown]] and long [[claws|talons]] on a hand, and holding a [[flaming sword]]. See post #1037362.
* After the Horus Heresy, sitting on the Golden Throne, usually as a corpse. See post #5024924.

title: yamato_(kancolle)
body:
[[Kantai Collection]]'s personification of the Japanese battleship [i]Yamato[/i]. Character design by [[Shizuma Yoshinori]], voiced by [[Taketatsu Ayana]].

She has [[long hair|long]] [[brown hair]] tied to a [[ponytail]], multiple [[cherry blossoms]] in her hair, and [[large breasts]]. 

Her default outfit consists of a [[white shirt]] with [[shoulder cutout]]s and a [[red sailor collar]], [[yellow neckerchief]], grey [[collar]] with a [[kikumon]], a "Z" [[signal flag]] [[armband]], [[red skirt|red]] [[pleated skirt]] with [[hip vent]]s, [[mismatched legwear|mismatched]] [[black socks]] (knee-length on her right, [[black thighhighs|thighhigh]] on her left), AP shells on her [[thigh strap]]s, and [[grey footwear|grey]] [[high heels|high-heeled]] [[rudder footwear]]. She also uses Type 91 AP shell caps as [[breast padding|breast pads]] as shown in her damaged arts. 

Her [[rigging]] consists a headpiece containing her two Type 21 [[radar]]s, and two large hull pieces in a half-circle and held by a funnel to her back, containing all three of her 46 cm triple gun mounts and either four triple 155 mm triple gun mounts (base) or two triple 155 and six 127 mm twin [[anti-aircraft gun]]s (kai). She also uses a [[red umbrella|red]] [[oil-paper umbrella]] patterned off her real-life tripod mast. 

Because the historical [i]Yamato[/i] had a career mostly based around impressing people, Yamato is often depicted as a shy and soft-spoken housewife. Yamato was historically referred to as the [[Hotel Yamato]], due to her relatively luxurious quarters and the fact that she was never used in combat until late in the war, when defeat was certain.

Yamato only fired her massive 460 mm guns in battle once during the Battle of Samar to finish off [[Gambier Bay (kancolle)|]]. This is the only confirmed kill of Yamato during her entire career. She was sunk on 7 April 1945 during [[Operation Ten-gou]], in which she was bombarded with dozens of bombs and torpedoes before being sunk off southern Kyushu.

title: richelieu_(kancolle)
body:
[[Kantai Collection]]'s personification of the lead ship of the French [i]Richelieu[/i]-class battleships. Character design by [[Akira (kadokawa)|]], voiced by [[Tanibe Yumi]].

She has light [[blue eyes]] and [[long hair|long]] [[blonde hair]] with a long lock [[long_hair_between_eyes|between her eyes]]. She has a [[mole under eye|mole under her left eye]] and another [[mole under mouth| below her mouth]].

Her outfit consists of a [[white beret]] with a red [[pom pom (clothes)|]] at the top, a [[two-tone dress|two-tone]] black-white-grey [[strapless dress]] with a [[belt]] under the breasts, a grey-black-red [[scarf]], black and white [[two-tone gloves]], a tricolore scarf tied on her left arm, black and white [[two-tone thighhighs]], and [[rudder footwear|rudder]]-styled [[loafers]].

The historical [i]Richelieu[/i] was laid down in 1935, launched in 1939 and still not fully complete at the start of [[World War II]]. She served both sides during the war. She began the war under [[Vichy]] France, notably helping fend off an Allied attack on Dakar. She joined the Allies in November 1942, and after a refit in New York was mostly employed in the Indian Ocean. After the war she served as a training ship and was eventually scrapped in 1968.

She is named after the "Red Eminence" [[Cardinal Richelieu]], a French clergyman and statesman.

title: yukikaze_(kancolle)
body:
[[Kantai Collection]]'s personification of the Japanese destroyer [i]Yukikaze[/i]. Character design by [[Shizuma Yoshinori]], voiced by [[Fujita Saki]].

She has [[short hair|short]] [[brown hair]], and [[brown eyes]]. 

Her default outfit consists of a [[white shirt|white]] [[long shirt|long]] [[sailor shirt]] (or [[white dress|white]] [[short dress|short]] [[sailor dress]]) with a [[yellow neckerchief]] and [[blue sailor collar]], [[black socks]], and [[grey footwear|grey]] [[high heels|high-heeled]] [[rudder footwear]]. Her [[rigging]] consists of her real-life fire control director as a [[mini hat]], Type 22 [[radar]] horns on the sides of her hair, a [[speaking tube headset]], 61 cm quad [[torpedo tubes]] to her back, 12.7 cm [[handgun]] mount, and [[binoculars]]. 

She is often compared to some sort of rodent (usually a [[Yukikaze (Hamster)|hamster]] or a [[yukikaze_(beaver)|beaver]]) due to the prominent upper teeth seen in her official art.

The historical [i]Yukikaze[/i] was transferred to the [[Taiwan|Republic of China]] as ROCS [[Tan Yang (Kancolle)|]] in 1947 as a war prize, where she served as the flagship of their navy. She was scrapped in 1970.

title: atlas_(fire_emblem)
body:
Playable character in [[Fire Emblem Gaiden]] and its [[Fire Emblem Echoes: Shadows of Valentia|remake]], who appears in [[Celica]]'s route.

A gruff but enthusiastic woodcutter from a Mountain Village, he joins Celica's army to rescue his brothers, who were kidnapped by [[Grieth (Fire Emblem)|]].

His original [i]Gaiden[/i] design featured [[short hair|short]], [[red hair]] with a [[blue shirt]] and a [[single pauldron]] on his right shoulder. In [i]Echoes[/i], Atlas' design has been updated to give him [[grey hair]] and slightly darker skin, as well as a much more [[muscular]] build. He now wears [[brown pants]] with [[yellow footwear]], and a small [[vest]] with [[fur trim]] exposing most of his chest.

title: camus_(fire_emblem)
body:
An antagonist who appears in [[Fire Emblem: Shadow Dragon and The Blade of Light]] and its remakes. Known for his unwavering loyalty to his homeland, Grust, he leads the country’s Sable Order and also rescued [[Nyna (Fire Emblem)|]] from captivity.

Later returns in [[Fire Emblem Gaiden]] and its remake as a playable character under the name [b]Zeke[/b], becoming an amnesiac Rigelian general who was rescued by [[Tatiana (Fire Emblem)|]] and fell in love with. After regaining his memories, Camus returns one final time in [[Fire Emblem: Mystery of The Emblem]] Book II, donning a mask and calling himself [b]Sirius[/b]. Afterwards, he vanishes from Archanea, presumably returning to Valentia where Tatiana waits for him.

All three of his identities have a consistent appearance: [[medium hair|medium]], [[blonde hair]], a [[black coat]] with white [[frills]] and [[gold trim]], a [[black cape]] with a red/magenta inside, and [[black footwear]] with [[black gloves]]. As Sirius, he additionally wears a white [[mask]].

title: crychic_(bang_dream!)
body:
Crychic is a disbanded band from [[Bang Dream! It's MyGO!!!!!]] anime.

It was initiated by [[Togawa Sakiko]] and [[Wakaba Mutsumi]] the year prior to the main anime timeline, when they were in middle school. The band disbanded after their one and only performance, after Sakiko abruptly left it.

[spoilers]Despite Soyo's efforts to keep the remaining members together, Tomori—shocked and blaming herself for Sakiko's leave—left soon after. With no lyricist, vocalist, or composer, the band ceased to function and effectively disbanded.[/spoilers]

Tomori, Soyo and Taki later went on to form [[MyGO!!!!! (bang dream!)|]], while Mutsumi and Sakiko eventually formed [[Ave Mujica (bang dream!)|]].

title: kazami_yuuka
body:
The "Flower Master of the Four Seasons".

Final Boss of [[Touhou]]'s [i][[Lotus Land Story]][/i] and later a recurring playable character, as well as the fourth [[Kazami Yuuka (PC-98)|PC-98]] generation character after [[Hakurei Reimu]], [[Kirisame Marisa]] and [[Alice Margatroid]] to reappear in the Windows generation (specifically in [i][[Phantasmagoria of Flower View]][/i]).

A highly dangerous youkai with the power to manipulate [[flower]]s, and reputed creator and original wielder of the [[Master Spark]] (which Marisa later "borrowed"). Hinted by [[Hieda no Akyuu]] to exhibit a rather polite facade, provided she or her flowers are not harmed. Once described by ZUN as "Youkai moe~", possibly meant as a pun given that the literal meaning of moe is "budding" and Yuuka controls flowers. Yuuka's place of residence is unknown in canon, but is generally assumed to be the [[Garden of the Sun]], where she tends a [[flower field|massive field]] of [[sunflower]]s, and it is known she used to occupy the Dream World mansion [[Mugenkan]] with her then-retainer [[Elly (touhou)|]]. Frequently portrayed in fan works as the [[sadism|Ultimate Sadistic Creature]] (USC), as a bloodthirsty psychopath, or as tsundere.  Usually some combination of the first two (or of all three).  Alternately, she is often depicted as lonely due to this reputation or as very friendly to [[Team 9 (touhou)|]] and other children.

She has [[short hair|short]] [[green hair]] with [[medium bangs|medium-length bangs]] and [[red eyes]], sometimes [[yellow eyes|yellow]]. Her outfit consists of an [[open vest|open]] [[plaid vest|plaid]] [[red vest]] over a [[long sleeves|long-sleeved]] [[collared shirt|collared]] [[white shirt]] tied with a [[yellow ascot]]. To complete her [[skirt set]] is a matching [[plaid skirt|plaid]] [[red skirt]] with [[frilled skirt|frills]] or [[plaid pants|plaid]] [[red pants]]. Her footwear is usually [[white socks]] with [[red shoes|red]] [[mary janes]] or [[brown boots]]. She usually carries her [[pink umbrella|pink]] [[parasol]].

h4. Appearance

* !post #5248036: Profile

h4. Fan-made Variations

* "Noukarin":[http://dic.pixiv.net/a/%E3%81%AE%E3%81%86%E3%81%8B%E3%82%8A%E3%82%93] (Farmer-Yuukarin): Originally a type of [[Yukkuri Shiteitte Ne]], unusually depicted with a full body instead of just as a head.  Now this word means Kazami Yuuka wearing a [[straw hat]].  Noukarin is frequently depicted with an acoustic [[guitar]] and/or with an almost impenetrable rural accent. 
* "Bakerin":[http://dic.pixiv.net/a/%E3%81%B9%E3%83%BC%E3%81%8B%E3%82%8A%E3%82%93] (Bakery-Yuukarin): A recent variant of Kazami Yuuka who makes [[bread]] in her own bakery named "[[Bakery]] Kazami".  "A certain tweet":http://twitter.com/matsurisyndrome/status/51104783376990208 caused this trend.
* [[Kazami Youka (yokochou)|]]: a younger and more upbeat version of Yuuka; from [[yokochou]]'s work.

title: maxim_gun
body:
A [[ammunition belt|belt-fed]] medium [b][[machine gun]][/b] invented in 1884 by Hiram Stevens Maxim and is historically the earliest example for an recoil-operated (or fully automatic) [[gun]], opposed to the manually operated [[gatling gun]] which has a hand[[crank]] for the user. It entered various armed conflicts since 1886, most notably the Two World Wars even until 21st century's [[Russo-Ukrainian war]]. Its tubular [[barrel shroud]] stores water for cooling the barrel.

The Maxim gun is usually mounted on wheeled carriages, vehicles, or [[tripod]]s, and sometimes equipped with a shield. A single personnel can fire the [[weapon]] , but a crew was required to carry spare ammunition, water, and a target spotter.

This tag also applies to its Russian/Soviet counterpart chambered in 7.62×54mmR, the PM M1910. Do not use the tag on any machine gun with a water-cooling jacket on its barrel like the [[Schwarzlose machine gun]] and [[Browning M1917]], and further research if the gun is a variant of the Maxim before tagging.

h4. Variants

* [[MG08]]
* [[Vickers machine gun]]
* [[pm1910|PM M1910]] 

h4. See also

* [[List of Weapons]]
* [[PM1910 (Girls' Frontline)]]

title: piapro_studio
body:
[b]Piapro[/b], short for "Peer Production", can refer to several entities owned by Crypton Future Media, Inc:
* [b]Piapro Family[/b], the group of characters owned by Crypton Future Media: [[MEIKO (vocaloid)|]], [[KAITO (vocaloid)|]], [[Hatsune Miku]], [[Kagamine Rin]] / [[kagamine_len|Len]], and [[Megurine Luka]]. Also referred to as "Cryptonloids" by fans.
* [b]piapro.jp[/b], a website for hosting art, music, and writing related to [[Vocaloid]], especially the Piapro Family.
* [b]Piapro Studio[/b], the name for two distinct vocal synth software:
** The original one is a plugin for digital audio workstations used for working with Vocaloids. It runs on the VOCALOID engine and is more-or-less a wrapped version of the VOCALOID software.
** The newer one is a standalone engine completely separate from VOCALOID and developed by Crypton themselves.

This tag mainly refers to voicebanks using the standalone Piapro engine:

title: neferpitou
body:
Character from [[Hunter x Hunter]], a chimera ant with ant, human and cat genes. Also known as [b]Pitou[/b].

No confirmed gender, although speaks with the male pronoun "boku". Has a prominent bust in both the anime and manga. Furthermore, wears female clothing in the manga and media related to the anime and was VA'd with a feminine voice. Was mistakenly referred to as "male" in an English translation of a official databook, leading to the misconception in the fandom that Pitou is confirmed male.

It can be presumed that the manga version was intended to be female, at least in appearance. As such, can be considered an archetypical catgirl.

Neferpitou's name is a combination of the Egyptian deity Nefertem and a character named Pitou in the French series "Caroline et ses Amis."

Voiced by: [[Fujimura Ayumi]] (Japanese), [[Sarah Anne Williams]] (English)

body:
English title: "My Next Life as a Villainess: All Routes Lead to Doom!"

An isekai story about a tomboyish otaku gamer who is reincarnated in to the villainous rival of the heroine in the game she played.  Being focused upon avoiding the Bad End flags of her story to the point of being oblivious to all else, the girl doesn't realize she's ruined the story by having a personality that out-heroines the original heroine and successfully builds a "reverse harem" for herself by mistake.

Illustrated by [[Hidaka Nami]].

title: nun
body:
A lay woman who has taken special vows committing her to a religious life, otherwise known as a religious sister. They must adopt a celibate life, refraining from marriage and sexual relationships - a religious sister takes part in a religious institution, while a nun lives a cloistered monastic life. They are recognized by their distinctive set of garments, called a habit. Christian ones can be additionally recognized by the appearance of a [[cross]] or [[crucifix]].

The term "nun" is applicable to Catholics – both Eastern and Western traditions – Orthodox Christians, Anglicans, Lutherans, Jains, [[buddhist nun|Buddhists]], and Taoists. Nuns can vary in appearance not just across each tradition, but within traditions as well; common subtypes of nuns across traditions include military nuns (or battle/combat/warrior nuns).

See [[traditional nun]] for the traditional modest Christian nun outfit, as opposed to the sexualized nun outfits typically seen in anime.

h4. Examples

body: Nameless mobs meant to fill out the ranks of Arius Branch School in [[Blue Archive]]. The sprite is seen with [[blonde hair|blonde]] [[twintails]] beneath her hood, her face covered by a [[gas mask]], and wearing a [[bulletproof vest]] bearing Arius' emblem above her white longcoat, alongside a matching [[armband]]. title: tibetan_fox_(kemono_friends)
body:
A [i][[Kemono Friends]][/i] character. She is one of many "Friends" in Japari Park.

The Tibetan Sand Fox ([i]Vulpes ferrilata[/i]) is a species of True Fox who lives in the Tibetan Plateau. It's infamous for its distinctive "stare", appearing almost human-like when looked at dead-on from the front with its squarish face and small almond eyes.

Tibetan Sand Fox (the Friend) shares the facial features of her original animal, simultaneously exhibiting a stong [[tsurime]] and a constant [[jitome]].

Fans often treat her and [[shoebill_(kemono_friends)|Shoebill]] as kindred spirits.

title: shinsoo_(tower_of_god)
body:
Shinsu (신수 (神水), shinsoo, literally "divine water") is a substance native to lifeforms within the Tower. It is produced by the Tower and flows through the surroundings like air.
Shinsu can be utilized in a multitude of ways, given adequate knowledge, skill, resistance, and natural talent. Through Shinsu, one can attain eternal youth, extended lifespans, halt the aging process, control natural elements and, even attain the powers of a god.

Shinsu is a very powerful, mysterious substance. It can be manipulated into [[water]], [[fire]] or [[light]]. It's possible to manipulate Shinsu into natural elements or unique forms ([[sword]], [[spear]], [[orb]]), a person must find "Shinsu Qualities" that suit them.

title: streets_of_rage
body:
[b]Bare Knuckle[/b] (ベア・ナックル 怒りの鉄拳 [i]Bea Nakkuru: Ikari no Tekken, "Bare Knuckle: Furious Iron Fist"[/i]) also known as [b]Streets of Rage[/b] is a side-scrolling beat 'em up [[video game]] released by [[Sega]] in 1991 for the [[Sega Mega Drive]].  

The game was created as a response to the [[Super Famicom]] ports of [[Final Fight]]. It is the first installment of the Bare Knuckle/Streets of Rage series which was followed by [[Streets of Rage 2]] (1992), [[Streets of Rage 3]] (1994) and [[Streets of Rage 4]] (2020). 

The game was also converted over to the [[Sega Game Gear]], Mega-CD and [[Sega Master System]]. In 2007, the game was released for the Wii's Virtual Console in North America and Europe, and in 2009 it was released for the iOS via the App Store. The game was again made available as part of [i]Sonic's Ultimate Genesis Collection[/i] in 2009 on both the [[PlayStation 3]] and [[Xbox 360]] consoles.

h4. Characters

* [[Blaze Fielding]]
* [[Axel Stone]]

title: kamishirasawa_keine
body:
"The History Eater"

Stage 3 mid-boss and boss as well as Extra Stage mid-boss of [[Touhou]]'s [[Imperishable Night]].

A were-hakutaku and schoolteacher with the ability to consume the history of [[Gensokyo]]'s Human Village to protect it from malicious youkai. Normally she has bluish-white hair and matching blue dress, except during a full moon when her hair becomes greenish-white, her dress turns green, and she grows horns. In this form, she can create and alter history.

Doujin works portray her as a [[teacher]] for some of the "child" characters in the series by whom she is feared for her punishment - a headbutt. She is also seen tutoring to [[Team 9 (touhou)|]] with predictable results. In canon, however, while she is a schoolteacher, she refuses to teach youkai. She is also a good friend to [[Fujiwara no Mokou]]. Many fans often pair her with [[Morichika Rinnosuke]] either as a childhood friend or a colleague due to their similar status as half-youkai.

h4. Appearance

American Thoroughbred racehorse. A competent racer in his own regard, with nine wins out of 31 starts, who was preferentially a turf runner. Best known for his career as a stud, having sired [[Sunday Silence (Racehorse)|]] and [[Goodbye Halo (Racehorse)|]] among many others.

Infrequently depicted as an [[Umamusume]] - often with a [[muzzle (mask)|]] or some sort of [[mask]]; the real Halo bit hard and often, and was frequently muzzled to prevent him from chewing on the fences or on an unsuspecting stablehand.

title: nezha
body:
Ambiguous character. Name written 哪吒.

A Taoist protection deity in [[chinese mythology|Chinese folk religion]]. His official Taoist name is [i]"Marshal of the Central Altar" (中壇元帥)[/i] and his title after he became a deity is [i]"Third Lotus Prince" (蓮花三太子)[/i].

After the death of his original body, his master [[Taiyi Zhenren]] used [[lotus root]]s and to revive him, he is thus often associated with lotus and has received many lotus-related nicknames.

He is often recognized as a [[trap]].

Nezha has frequently appeared in Chinese mythology and ancient Chinese literature such as "Fengshen Yanyi":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Investiture_of_the_Gods and [[Journey to the West]].

title: dawn_of_war
body:
[b]Dawn of War[/b] is a real time strategy game series for PC and Mac, developed by Relic Entertainment based on the [[Warhammer 40K]] table top game. The Dawn of War games were well received by gamers and critics and help introduced the 40k franchise to new fans.

The first Dawn of War was released in 2004 and had four playable factions, [[Adeptus Astartes|Space Marines]], [[Ork (Warhammer)|]]s, [[Eldar]] and [[Chaos Space Marine]]s. In the game's single player campaign, the [[Blood Ravens]] 3rd Company led by Captain [[Gabriel Angelos]], head to the planet Tartarus as help after the planet is invaded by Orks. However, Gabriel learns something is amiss when the Eldar led by Farseer [[Macha (Warhammer)|]] and the [[Alpha Legion]] Chaos Spaces Marines are there on the planet as well.

title: mystia_lorelei
body:
The "Night Sparrow." Stage 2 mid-boss and boss of [[Touhou]]'s [i][[Imperishable Night]][/i] and a playable character in [i][[Phantasmagoria of Flower View]][/i].

An egocentric night sparrow youkai who can induce confusion and night-blindness with her song. She dislikes [[yakitori]] (grilled chicken) and has set up a grilled lamprey eel stand in protest, convincing blinded travellers that her eels cure blindness (she cures them on the spot). 

She is best known, however, for having been reputedly devoured by [[Saigyouji Yuyuko]] during IN, only to reappear in PoFV, landing her a place in [[Team 9 (touhou)|]], a posse of low-tier Touhou characters. Her more recent association with [[Kasodani Kyouko]] as part of [[Choujuu Gigaku]], as well as the increased prominence of her food stand, have loosened her association with Team 9 somewhat.

Contrary to accusations of being illiterate by [[Shameimaru Aya]] in an interview from [[Bohemian Archive in Japanese Red]], she merely has poor eyesight, based an appearance in [[Touhou Sangetsusei]] where she uses a magnifying lens to help her read.

title: sonya_(fire_emblem_gaiden)
body:
A playable character from [[Fire Emblem Gaiden]] and its remake, [[Fire Emblem Echoes: Shadows of Valentia]], who is recruitable in [[Celica (Fire Emblem)|]]’s route. She is [[Jedah (Fire Emblem)|]]’s daughter, who seeks vengeance against her father for turning her older sisters, [[Marla (Fire Emblem)|]] and [[Hestia (Fire Emblem)|]], into witches. She also serves the Bandit King [[Grieth (Fire Emblem)|]], alongside [[Deen (Fire Emblem Gaiden)|]], but secretly hates him.

Her original [i]Gaiden[/i] design gave Sonya [[long hair|long]], [[red hair]] with a [[two-tone cape]] and a [[red dress]]. Her redesign in [i]Echoes[/i] retains many of these features, but recolors her hair to purple and changing its style. Her dress also now has a red and black pattern, and her cape is now purple on the inside. Additionally, Sonya possesses a [[circlet]] and a pair of diamond-shaped [[earrings]].

Not to be confused with [[Sonia (fire emblem: the blazing blade)|]] from [[Fire Emblem: The Blazing Blade]].

title: megatron
body:
[b]Megatron[/b] is one of the most well-known villains of the [[Transformers]] franchise. He is the powerful and merciless leader of the antagonist faction, the evil [[Decepticon]]s.

His original alternate mode is a grey and silver [[Walther P38]] [[handgun]] with several attachments. Due to changes in toy safety laws, contemporary versions of Megatron have had to design new alternate modes, usually having him become some sort of [[military]] vehicle such as a [[tank]] or [[helicopter]]. Modern incarnations, such as the [[transformers (live action)|live action movie]], have had him become an 'alien' craft rather than an Earth-based vehicle.

Megatron's first G1 design was created by designer Ono Kojin for the Japanese [i]Microchange[/i] [[transformation]] [[robot]] [[toy]] series in the early 80s.

[quote]Motto: [i]"Peace through tyranny...!!!"[/i][/quote]

h4. Alternate Versions

* Galvatron - [spoilers]the upgraded form [[Unicron]] gives to Megatron in the G1 movie, and the name used for his upgraded form in several later series as well. As[/spoilers] Galvatron is sometimes depicted as a completely separate character, at times existing alongside Megatron, images of Galvatron alone should not be tagged as [[Megatron]].
* [[Optimal Megatron]]  - Megatron's upgraded form in [[Beast Machines]].
* [[Gigatron]] - The Decepticon leader in [[Transformers Car Robots|Car Robots]], who was renamed to Megatron in the English dub.
* [[Megatron (IDW)]] - the [[the transformers (idw)|IDW Comics]] depiction of Megatron, most notable for his sincere attempts at atonement and defection to the [[Autobot|Autobots]].
* [[Megatron (Prime)]] - the depiction of Megatron in [[Transformers Prime]], with a design inspired by his appearance in the [[transformers (live action)|live action films]].
* [[Megatron (Shattered Glass)]] - the depiction of Megatron in the [[transformers shattered glass|Shattered Glass]] AU, in which he is the noble leader of the benevolent [[decepticon|Decepticons]].
* [[Megatron (Kotobukiya Bishoujo)]] -  a [[humanization|humanized]] [[genderswap (mtf)|female]] version of Megatron from the [[Kotobukiya Bishoujo]] figure line.

h4. See also

* [spoilers][[Galvatron]][/spoilers]
* [[Megatron (Beast Wars)]] - The [[Predacon]] leader in [[Beast Wars]], transforms into a [[tyrannosaurus rex]]. Despite sharing the same name as the original character, is a separate entity existing in a different time period from the original.

title: predacon
body:
"Predacon" can refer to three groups of [[robot|robots]] within the  [[Transformers]] franchise.

-A subfaction of [[Decepticon|Decepticons]] in the [[Transformers: Generation 1|original Transformers series]] first appearing in 1986. They are a group of aggressive warriors that turn into robotic animals, and are capable of combining to form the giant robot [[Predaking]]. They consist of Razorclaw, Rampage, Divebomb, Headstrong, and Tantrum. This group is referred to as "Animatrons" in the Japanese version.

-The main villain faction of the [[Beast Wars]] series. Descendants of the Decepticons, they tend to become animals such as reptiles, insects, amphibians, and crustaceans. They are led by the [[Megatron (Beast Wars)|Predacon Megatron]], who shares his name with the original Decepticon Megatron but is a separate entity. In Japan, they are referred to as Destrons, the same name used for the Decepticons in most Japanese releases.

-A faction in the third and final season of [[Transformers Prime]]. These Predacons were a form of prehistoric life on [[Cybertron]] before going extinct. They were revived in the present day by Decepticon cloning experiments to use as an army. As the third season of Prime was not dubbed in Japan, the Predacons were given a different role and backstory as part of [[Transformers_Go|Transformers Go!]] instead.

title: effects_pedal
body:
A foot-operated device, typically used by players of [[electric guitar]] (but in fact usable by any musical [[instrument]] or device with an audio output), plugged into the signal path between the instrument and the [[amplifier]] in order to alter the properties of emanating sound.

Single effects pedals can be of various types including chorus, reverb, overdrive, distortion, wah-wah, pitch-shift and so on. It is common to see several effects pedals linked in series on a live stage, often grouped onto a [[pedal board]], where they can be toggled in any combination. Multi-effects pedals combine many of these together into the same box.

h4. Examples

* !post #6005365: Delay, overdrive and distortion pedals.
* !post #4482110

title: jyu_viole_grace
body:
In Part II, Baam has grown taller. As Viole, his hair has grown into a narrow [[ponytail]] reaching down to his waist, with his [[hair over eyes| bangs often obscuring his eyes]] . After the events of the Workshop Battle, Baam cut his hair back to the length it was in Part I. 

Part II:

● Slayer Robes: He wears a long [[black robe]] with the FUG designs on the inside. He wears these again as he took the 29th Floor test with the rest of FUG but with a slight color alteration and no FUG mark.

● Pinstripe Suit: After the Shinsu Strengthening test, he wears a [[purple suit | purple]] and [[black suit | black]] [[striped suit]] with formal [[black pants]].

● Designer Clothing: On the 21st Floor test, he wears a [[black hoodie]] with orange strings and [[jeans]].
Casual Wear: He wears a light-blue and [[white shirt | white]]  [[shirt]] with [[brown pants]].

title: shockwave_(transformers)
body:
A character from the [[Transformers]] science fiction franchise.

[b]Shockwave[/b] is an evil [[Decepticon]], a sentient [[alien]] [[robot]] that can transform into a purple [[cybertron]]ian [[energy gun]]. Modern incarnations have had him become a futuristic alien [[tank]] instead.

He is equipped with a powerful [[arm cannon]]. Shockwave is also one of the few Transformers without a face, having only a yellow sensor "eye" in his head.

In [[Japan]] his name was changed to [b]Laserwave[/b] (レーザーウェーブ).

[quote]Motto: [i]"Clarity of thought before rashness of action...".[/i][/quote]

h4.See also

* "Transformers Wiki (G1 version)":http://tfwiki.com/wiki/Shockwave_%28G1%29

title: arcee
body:
A character from the [[Transformers]] science fiction franchise, first appearing 1986's [i]The Transformers: The Movie[/i].

[b]Arcee[/b] is an heroic [[Autobot]], a sentient [[alien]] female [[robot]] that can transform into a pink and white Cybertronian convertible hover [[car]].

In later iterations of the franchise her alternate mode is sometimes a [[motorcycle]]. Some versions as [[Transformers Prime]] choose to make her blue instead of pink.

[quote]Motto: [i]"Looks are always deceiving...".[/i][/quote]

title: mormonism
body:
For posts referencing Mormonism and the adherent(s) of the Latter Day Saints movement. 

Mormonism is a non-trinitarian, restorationist branch of [[Christianity]] founded by Joseph Smith in the 1820s Western New York, USA. It focuses on the living [[jesus|Christ]] and His resurrection, rather than His crucifixion. Thus Mormons do not typically use the cross symbol. Their scripture uses the Book of Mormon alongside the Bible.

Considered controversial by mainstream Christian branches due to notable [[religious missionary|missionary]] activity, dietary restrictions on coffee, and other factors.

h4. External links

* Wikipedia: "Mormonism":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/mormonism

title: iwanaga_ariya
body:
[b]The Princess of Permanence[/b]

Stage 6 boss of [[Fossilized Wonders]].

Iwanaga is based on the mythical Goddess of Immortality, Iwanagahime. She has [[short_hair|short]], [[brown hair]], is [[barefoot]], and has [[red eyes]]. She wears a [[half mask]] over her left eye, and her [[skirt]] is made of [[stone]]. Golden [[bone|bones]] drape over her clothes. She has [[asymmetrical_wings|asymmetrical]], [[skeletal wings]], with [[fire]] emanating from her left wing, and [[disembodied_eye|disembodied eyes]] covering her right wing. 

The pyramid-shaped Lunar Capital facility, Asama Joue(Impurity-Cleansing) Mountain, was originally her shrine, where she was worshipped alongside [[Yuiman_asama|Yuiman]]. Iwanaga had the power of perpetuity, which is the power to maintain the same shape, as long-lived as stone. The Lunarians adored that eternal power, but she refused the idea of joining their ranks. The power of perpetuity is the power of rejection. Even with her shrine being taken over, she continued to reject them until she was eventually sealed. 

During the events of Fossilized Wonders, she was unsealed by [[Watatsuki_no_Toyohime|Toyohime]]. She was ordered to freeze all of Gensokyo, in order to stop the impurity(=life information) coming from The Outside World. She agreed to cooperate with [[Yagokoro_Eirin|Eirin]] and [[Watatsuki_no_Toyohime|Toyohime]] as part of their plans to save The Lunar Capital, and later on be defeated by the protagonists to save Gensokyo, so that [[Yuiman_Asama|Yuiman]] could be saved.

h4. Appearance

* !post #9811576: Profile

h4. External links

* "Touhou wiki: Iwanaga Ariya":https://en.touhouwiki.net/wiki/Ariya_Iwanaga

title: axl_ro
body:
Axl RO is a secondary antagonist featured in the seventh part of the [[JoJo No Kimyou Na Bouken]] series, [[Steel Ball Run]].

He is a [[Stand (jojo)|]] user, powering his [[Civil War (Stand)|]] with guilt.

Axl appears to be a middle-aged man of average to above-average height and [[toned male|medium build]]. Darkness (either shadow, paint or a tattoo) covers his face to just below his eyes and in mirrored, hook-like tribal marks on his cheeks; save for a scattering of dots.

Over a light, drooping rag, he wears a thick, round [[m1 helmet|military helmet]] covered by a net. He wears a thick wide-necked top, bearing four dark rectangular patches between his shoulders and elbows on his long sleeves. His chest is overlaid with a V-shaped piece from which hang layers of squares; and he wears dark, [[knee boots]].

title: high-ended_braid
body:
The opposite of [[low-braided long hair]], where the [[braid]] ends higher than usual and takes up less than half of the hair length, leaving more of the hair hanging loose.

Not to be confused with [[french braided ponytail]] and [[french braided twintails]]. French braids are hair braided on the scalp, it's normal for them to end under the scalp.

title: x-ray
body:
Seeing inside or through a normally opaque barrier, as if by x-ray vision. Examples: skin, bone, armor, metal containers, concrete walls...

Typically rendered as a partially transparent overlay, or a cut-out. The internal and external views should always be overlapping. Rule of thumb: It's [[x-ray]] if Superman could see it with x-ray vision.

Use [[x-ray film]] for the images taken with actual [[x-ray machine]]s (or any medical device that takes cross-section images).

h4. Disambiguation

* [[Wet]], sheer, or clear clothing only qualifies as [[see-through clothes]] because it has natural transparency.
* A cut-out internal view separated from the main image only qualifies as [[cross-section]] because it doesn't show the external barrier.
* [[Slime girl]] is a class by itself.

h4. See also

* [[cross-section]]
* [[cut-away]]
* [[internal cumshot]]
* [[invisible]] (for completely invisible people)
** [[invisible man]]  (for hentai)
* [[revealing layer]]
* [[reverse x-ray]]
* [[transparent]]
* [[x-ray vision]]
** [[x-ray glasses]]

Japanese [[horse|racehorse]]. Sired by [[Gold Ship (racehorse)|]] and foaled by [[Meisho Tsubakuro (racehorse)|]]. He contrasts his sire's chasing running style by being a front-runner instead.

Although he was obviously talented enough to win graded races, he completely flubbed his classic appearences and only made a real breakthrough after being paired with [[Take Yutaka]], finally earning him a G1 at the 2025 [[Takarazuka Kinen]], a race his sire particularly excelled at, during Father's Day.

title: ookawara_kunio
body:
[b]Ookawara Kunio[/b] (大河原 邦男, December 26, 1947—) is a veteran mechanical designer in the anime industry. A mechanical designer is similar to a character designer, but the design is for robots, ships, and other mechanical items found in a particular show. 

Ookawara was the first in the industry to be specifically credited as a mechanical designer. He designed [[mecha]] for the [[Gundam]] and Brave Series franchises, as well as those of numerous [[Super Robot]] and [[mecha|Real Robot]] shows.

He was born and currently lives in Inagi, Tokyo, where he works out of a studio in his home.

h4. Famous Designs

* [[RX-78-2 Gundam]]/[[Zaku II]]/[[Gelgoog]] and many others ([[Mobile Suit Gundam]])
* [[Guntank]] ([[Mobile Suit Gundam]])
* [[Zaku II S Char Custom]] ([[Mobile Suit Gundam]])
* [[Gouf]] ([[Mobile Suit Gundam]])
* [[Big Zam]] ([[Mobile Suit Gundam]])

title: doomguy
body:
The player character of the [[Doom (series)|]] series. Also known as the [b]Doom Marine[/b] and the [b]Doom Slayer[/b]. Usually depicted as a [[muscular male|muscular]] [[space marine]] with green [[armor]] and a [[helmet]].

Not much is known about Doomguy's life prior to the Doom games, but it is known that he was transferred to Mars in the first place because he had assaulted a superior officer for ordering soldiers to fire upon civilians.

In the classic Doom games, the story actually started when Mars has gone to heck, the demons and its arches of hell had began spreading in Phobos in the moon of Mars, turning the entire moon into a platform of Hell. From there, Doomguy began his quest to return to Earth and slayed many demons ranging from a pistol to a shotgun and a BFG-9000.

Doomguy has a pet rabbit called Daisy, but this in turn began his rage when the demons killed the rabbit and continues slaying demons in Earth (as it continues in Thy Flesh Consumed, Episode 4 of the first game).

In Doom II, Doomguy rescues most of the civilians from earth in order to close Hell once and for all. The story continues from Doom 64 (whereas he chose to remain in Hell forever so no demons can enter Earth or Mars but this eventually failed due to "The Lost Levels" expansion, where he got teleported by the Sister Resurrector.) and the Modern era of Doom 2016 and Doom Eternal (Itself a remake of Doom II).

h4. See also

* [[Doom (series)]]

h4. External links

* "Doom Wiki: Doom's protagonist":https://doomwiki.org/wiki/Doom%27s_protagonist

title: locusta_(fate)
body:
Assassin-class Servant introduced in [[Fate/Grand Order]]'s [[Lilim Harlot]] event. [[Nero Claudius (fate)|]]' personal poisons expert and purportedly history's first serial killer. She was responsible for the assassinations of Nero's father Claudius at Agrippina the Younger's behest, and Claudius' son Britannicus, born from his third wife Valeria Messalina, at Nero's behest. Along with Nero's other 'favorites', Locusta was eventually executed for her crimes following Nero's suicide.

title: kujirada_(yu-gi-oh!)
body:
Kujirada is a [[Yu-Gi-Oh!]] character. He is a student belonging to Domino High School. Appearance-wise, he is a [[fat|chubby boy]] with [[green hair]].

His story is portrayed differently in Season Zero and the manga, as the manipulator behind his schemes are different characters. In the manga, the virtual pet has kept him up all night through its constant demands for food. The virtual pet begins craving other virtual pets to eat, so Kujirada folds to the pet's demands and begins abducting other pets to satisfy these needs. Once the pet is defeated, Kujirada is freed. Despite losing a powerful pet, Kujirada could finally get some rest.

In Season Zero, the manipulator is Haiyama, who treats Kujirada like a pet.

title: rip_current
body:
A rip current is a strong, localized, and narrow current of water that moves directly away from the shore by cutting through the lines of breaking waves, like a river flowing out to sea. The force of the current in a rip is strongest and fastest next to the surface of the water.  Swimmers caught in a rip current and unaware of what is happening may exhaust themselves attempting to swim against the current.  Rip currents are one of the leading causes of rescues by lifeguards and result in deaths every year.

h4. External links

* "Wikipedia: Rip current":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rip_current]

title: menstruation
body:
[i]Not to be confused with [[defloration]][/i]

Menstruation is the shedding of the uterine lining (endometrium). It occurs on a regular basis in reproductive-age females of certain mammal species. Overt menstruation (where there is [[bleeding]] from the [[uterus]] through the [[pussy|vagina]]) is found primarily in humans and close evolutionary relatives such as chimpanzees.

title: upturned_eyes
body:
When a character's eyes are pointed upwards relative to their face. This is often done to look cute, coy, childish, timid, submissive, or pleading.

This expression is sometimes accompanied by the [[head down|head tilted downward]], sometimes with face facing forward but [[looking up]], often occurs alongside [[raised eyebrows]]. It also occurs when a character is [[looking at viewer|looking at the viewer]], but is below their eye-level (such as often the case with [[fellatio]]).

This is different from [[rolling eyes]] or eyes rolled back in the head (as in [[ahegao]]) in that in this case something is actively being focused on and looked at. This is similar to [[sanpaku]] in that the white sclera of their eyes might be visible to three of four sides of their irises, but in this tag refers to a soft, gentle expression, whereas [[sanpaku]] refers to a shocked, angry, detatched, or unhinged expression.

h4. Examples

* !post #459094
* !post #9734437
* !post #2999790
* !post #5819696

h4. See also

title: donkey_kong
body:
The title character and main villain of the arcade game [[Donkey Kong (1981 Game)|]], an early arcade hit for [[Nintendo]]. [[Mario]] has to fend off his barrels to rescue [[Pauline (Mario)|]]. This version would later become [[Cranky Kong]].

In later games, such as in [[Donkey Kong Country]], the name would be passed onto his grandson, becoming a reoccurring character in the [[Mario (series)|]] spinoff games.

He has had three different main appearances: the first was his original appearance, where he is often paired with [[Donkey Kong Jr.]] and portrayed as a villain; the second is often called his 'Rareware' appearance, which he received from Donkey Kong Country onward; his third and current appearance is an adaptation of his original, appearing first in [[The Super Mario Bros. Movie]], [[Mario Kart World]], and [[Donkey Kong Bananza]].

Japanese [[horse|racehorse]]. Sired by [[Bago (racehorse)|]] (a winner of the Prix de L'Arc de Triomphe) and foaled by [[Chronologist (racehorse)|]] (from [[Kurofune (Racehorse)|]]). She is the younger sister of [[Normcore (Racehorse)|]], who is also individually successful as a racer.

She was a particularly dark gray mare in her prime, likely born as Black or Brown, with an irregular star or stripe marking shaped like a Greater-than sign or a right single guillemet, and a pastern on her front left leg.

She started her career in a still growing state and most of her major wins were punctuated by sudden large weight gains. She is the winner of the 2019 Shuka Sho, the 2020 and 2021 Takarazuka Kinen and the 2020 Arima Kinen. She was paired with [[Kitamura Yuuichi (jockey)|]] up until near the end of her career, upon which [[Christophe Lemaire]] took his place.

She became [[Chrono Genesis (Umamusume)|an official]] [[Umamusume]] in time for the 4th Anniversary of the game along with [[Gran Alegria (Umamusume)|many]] [[Loves Only You (Umamusume)|of]] [[Curren Bouquetd'or (Umamusume)|her]] [[Almond Eye (Umamusume)|illustrious]] [[Lucky Lilac (Umamusume)|rivals]].

title: letty_whiterock
body:
The "Leftover of Winter". Stage 1 boss of [[Touhou]]'s [[Perfect Cherry Blossom]].

A seasonal yuki onna in control of cold, leading to her doujin portrayal as friends with [[Cirno]]. She is only visible during winter, but her status on other times of the year is debatable (either she melts or hibernates somewhere). She is infamous, however, for her large [[hitbox]], which led to jokes about her being [[fat]] and her pictures with a [[curvy]] or [[plump]] figure and [[large breasts]]. The ornament often drawn on her chest is a [[lapel pin]].

h4. Appearance

title: yakushiji_suzaku
body:
A former [[Virtual YouTuber]] and first-generation member of [[Holostars]]. His appearance seems intimidating, but he’s a cheerful, playful man who enjoyed messing with people. He also has something of a comedic sociopathic streak, when he realized he could get rid of everyone in [[Japan]] to turn it into an uninhabited island that he wanted. FPS games were his specialty.

Retired on March 6th, 2020 without a reason, though fans guess it was due to low engagement. As he graduated before Holostars started receiving attention, information about him is scarce, not helped by his channel removing all of his archives upon [[Tsukishita Kaoru]]’s own retirement.

He has [[white hair]] with [[hair between eyes]] and [[yellow eyes]]. His outfit consists of a [[white shirt|white]] [[unbuttoned shirt|unbuttoned]] [[collared shirt]], [[black shirt|black]] [[undershirt]], [[black pants]], a [[red kimono|red]] [[kimono on shoulders]], and [[red shoes|red]] [[sneakers]]. He also wears an [[omamori]] on his [[belt]] and a [[gold bracelet|gold]] [[bead bracelet]]. He carries a [[katana]] called Shuchoumaru.

title: wanshi:_hypnos_(pgr)
body:
A frame of [[Wanshi (pgr)|]] from [[Punishing: Gray Raven]].

h4. Appearance

In the Hypnos frame, Wanshi has [[short hair|short]] [[white hair]] that is usually [[unkempt]] or [[messy hair|messy]] (possibly [[cowlick]]s), he has [[yellow eyes]] but the left eye is [[one eye covered|covered]] by his [[hair over one eye|hair]]. Wears a [[sleep mask]] on his forehead, he is usually depicted tired, [[sleeping]] and/or has [[bags under eyes]]. Has a single [[mole under mouth]] (left chin) and two [[mechanical legs]] that attaches above the knee.

His apparels consist of a [[black shirt|black]] [[undershirt]] with a [[white jacket|white]] [[open jacket]], the jacket's [[long sleeves]] can be coated in [[digital camouflage]] depending on awakening level of the character. Wears a pair of [[white pants]], with [[thigh strap]], [[thigh pouch]] and [[belt pouch]]. Other possible accessories including [[dog tags]], [[chest harness]] and a [[walkie-talkie]].

Uses a [[sniper rifle]] as main weapon and a pistol [[handgun]] as side arm.

title: kiss_players
body:
A 2006 installment in the [[Transformers]] franchise consisting of a manga, toyline, and radio drama. The series is named for the female human characters who have the ability to fuse with Cybertronians by kissing them. Each release in the toyline included both a transformer and a figure of their human companion.

The series is viewed with disdain by many Western fans (and some Japanese) due to its usage of sexually suggestive imagery and scenes where the young-looking female characters are placed in questionable scenarios involving Transformers. It is also notable for retconning several spinoffs and standalone series (including [i][[Transformers Car Robots|Car Robots]][/i]) into the Japanese G1 continuity.

title: brawly_(pokemon)
body:
[b]Brawly[/b], known as [b]Touki[/b] in Japan, is a character introduced in [[pokemon|Pokémon]] [[pokemon rse|Ruby and Sapphire]].

This Gym Leader is skilled with Fighting-type Pokémon and also trains his body to surf. He moved from Kanto to Hoenn for the waves. His signature Pokémon is [[Hariyama]].

In his original appearance, he has [[blue eyes]] and [[medium hair|medium-length]] [[spiked hair|spiked]] [[blue hair]]. He wears a [[short sleeves|short-sleeve]] [[orange shirt]] over a [[black shirt|black]] [[undershirt]], [[baggy pants|baggy]] [[blue pants|blue]] [[capri pants]], and [[grey shoes|grey]] [[two-tone shoes|and]] [[orange shoes|orange]] [[shoes]].

In [[Pokemon ORAS]] he undergoes a redesign, including [[dark-skinned male|darker skin]] and [[long hair|longer hair]]. He wears [[black-framed eyewear|black-framed]] [[orange-tinted eyewear|orange-tinted]] [[sunglasses]] [[eyewear on head|on his head]], a [[skin tight]] [[black shirt]], and [[black gloves|black]] [[fingerless gloves]].

title: stark_(sousou_no_frieren)
body:
Stark is a Human Warrior. After his village was attacked by Demons, he fled and was taken in by [[Eisen (sousou no frieren)|]], before eventually joining [[Frieren]]'s party as their vanguard.

Stark has [[short hair|short]] spiky, [[black hair|black]] and [[red hair|red]] [[two-tone hair|dual-tone hair]] and [[orange eyes]]. He typically wears a [[collared shirt|collared]] [[black shirt|black]] [[sleeveless shirt]] along with [[black pants]] and a [[white sash]] [[waist sash|around his waist]], and wraps [[bandaged arm|bandages around his arms]]. When he is out, he wears a [[red coat]] and [[black gloves|black]] [[fingerless gloves]], and straps his weapon, a large [[battle axe]], [[weapon on back|to his back]] with a [[belt]]. He wears a silver [[bracelet]] that he received as a birthday gift from [[Fern (sousou no frieren)|]] on his wrist.

He has a [[scar on forehead|large scar on his forehead]] that he got from Eisen when he was hit for being cowardly during an argument.

title: zoom_layer
body:
An additional layer that magnifies part of the illustration, usually a character. It's a common technique used for backgrounds in character art. 

There are sometimes small alterations, such as:

* The colors being muted, partially transparent, or in [[greyscale]].
* Simple image transformations, such as being mirrored, scaled, or rotated.
* A character having a different facial expression.

In these cases, the tag [[different zoom layer]] should also be added.

If the layer cannot be derived in some way from the base image, such as having a different perspective, a different pose, different attire, or other characters, it's a [[projected inset]] instead.

For the "zoom layer" effect used on [[stage]]s by projecting the performance on background [[screen]]s, use [[screen zoom]] instead.

h4. See also
* [[Character Background]]
* [[Tag group:Backgrounds]]
* [[Tag group:Image composition]]

title: daimon_masaru_(digimon_savers)
body:
The protagonist of [[Digimon Savers]], a hot-headed self-titled street fighter and partner of [[Agumon (Digimon Savers)|]]. 

Has a reputation for being disproportionately, almost superhumanly strong, as he repeatedly punches out Digimon the size of buildings and even destroyed [[Craniummon]]'s spear, Claíomh Solais, with his bare hands. Some even joke that he's stronger than any Ultimate-level Digimon. 

In English media, Masaru is referred to by the dub name [b]Marcus Damon[/b].

title: kromer_(project_moon)
body:
Main antagonist of [[Limbus Company]]'s Canto III.

Leader of N Corp's Inquisition. Upholding her ideology of loving purity, she despises anyone with prosthetics, leading an army of inquisitors to kill those they deem a 'heretic'.

[spoiler]Formerly, [[Sinclair (Project Moon)|]]'s classmate and friend, she was responsible for the death of his family.[/spoiler]

title: q-transformers
body:
A line of [[Transformers]] toys released exclusively in Japan that consisted of [[chibi|super deformed]] versions of the characters who transformed into licensed vehicles, based on the proportions of [[Choro-Q]] toys. The initial releases were mostly designed based on the [[transformers (live action)|live action movies]], but later releases included designs based on their [[transformers: generation 1|G1]] appearances.

A mobile game and series of anime shorts were created to tie in to the toyline.

The toyline featured crossovers with [i][[Neon Genesis Evangelion]][/i], [i][[Peanuts (comic)|]][/i], [i][[Hello Kitty]][/i], and [i][[Kamiusagi Rope]][/i].

body:
A character from the [[Transformers]] [[science_fiction|sci-fi]] franchise, first appearing in 1986's [i]The Transformers: The Movie[/i].

[b]Unicron[/b] is an evil, all powerful, massive and sentient [[alien]] [[robot]] that transforms into a yellow and silver metallic [[planet]]. He is a god of evil, neither [[Autobot]] nor [[Decepticon]]. He is in a constant struggle against his benevolent brother [[Primus (transformers)|]].

title: transformers:_the_war_within
body:
A group of comic miniseries in the [[Transformers]] franchise, published by Dreamwave productions in 2002-2004. It is set in the beginning of the war between the [[autobot|Autobots]] and [[decepticon|Decepticons]]. The comic is notable for introducing many characters with designs based on how they appeared before arriving on Earth, as well as the first appearance of [[The Fallen]] in any Transformers media.

The War Within was published as a six-issue miniseries, later getting two sequel miniseries titled The Dark Ages and The Age Of Wrath. Due to Dreamwave's bankruptcy in 2004, The Age Of Wrath only had three of its six issues published.

title: transformers_(marvel)
body:
The official comic series produced by [[Marvel]] for the [[Transformers: Generation_1|original run]] of the [[Transformers]] franchise. While it ran alongside the cartoon series, it was a separate story.

The comic ran monthly from 1984 to mid-1991 before its cancellation, for 80 issues. In the UK, the comic ran weekly for 332 issues, with additional UK-original stories and added comic stories from other Hasbro franchises. The first 55 US issues were written by Bob Budiansky, while the last 25 issues and additional UK stories were written by Simon Furman.

The comic briefly resumed as Transformers: Generation 2 for a short 12-issue run between 1993 and 1994 written by Furman.

The Marvel series is notable for having several differences in characterization between it and the cartoon series, as well as a focus on several later characters who appeared in the toyline after the cartoon had stopped production in 1987.

[b]See also:[/b]
[[The Transformers (Idw)|Transformers (IDW)]]: Transformers comic series produced under IDW Publishing, some of which were also written by Simon Furman
[[g.i._joe|G.I. JOE]]: Another franchise based on a Hasbro toyline that had a Marvel comic, which had several crossovers with the Transformers comic

title: daring_tact_(racehorse)
body:
[tn]"Daring" from her dam's name. "Tact" is short for "tactics".[/tn]

[table]
[body]
[tr][td]Sire:[/td][td][[Epiphaneia (racehorse)|]][/td][/tr]
[tr][td]Grandsire:[/td][td][[Symboli Kris S (racehorse)|]][/td][/tr]
[tr][td]Dam:[/td][td][[Daring Bird (racehorse)|]][/td][/tr]
[tr][td]Damsire:[/td][td][[King Kamehameha (racehorse)|]][/td][/tr]
[/body]
[/table]

Real-life Japanese Racehorse. Sired by [[Epiphaneia (racehorse)|]] (from [[Symboli Kris S (racehorse)|]] and foaled by [[Cesario (racehorse)|]], a daughter of [[Special Week (racehorse)|]]) and foaled by [[Daring Bird (racehorse)|]]. She became famous as the first undefeated Japanese Triple Tiara in 2020 but victory eluded her afterwards. She went on a hiatus after the 2022 Queen Elizabeth II Cup in [[Hong Kong]] due to injuries, resting for over a year before returning to race only to stop again due to more injuries after the 2022 Japan Cup. She was eventually retired on October 6 2023 due to her leg issues not having improved since then.

She is a brown mare with a small star marking (itself roughly shaped like a star) and no leg markings.

She is also famous for her firsts in [[Umamusume]], being the first horse to be implemented while still being active as well as the first triple tiara to be unveiled.

She is also infamous for her [[meme|memetic]] "interview" during her hiatus which features her taking a bath and making a face while subtitles rolls below her, which makes her look like she's mouthing what the actual interviewee is saying. This led to jokes about her being the voice actress of her own Umamusume counterpart (e.g.: post #5722302).

title: heathcliff_(wuthering_heights)
body:
Main protagonist of [i][[Wuthering Heights]][/i].

Once an orphaned boy adopted into the titular manor by the Earnshaw family. He would became close to [[Catherine Earnshaw|Catherine]], however, the ensuing abuse from her brother, [[Hindley Earnshaw]] and [[Edgar Linton]], and ultimately, Catherine's marriage to Edgar led to Heathcliff fleeing the manor and one day swear revenge against them.

3 decades later, Heathcliff took over Wuthering Heights as its new master by exploiting Hindley's alcoholism and gambling addiction, convincing him to mortgage the manor to cover the incurred losses, Hindley would later succumb to his alcoholism.

title: chloe_von_einzbern
body:
A character who first appears in the manga [[Fate/Kaleid Liner Prisma Illya]] and its anime adaptation.

She is a [[dark_skin|dark skinned]] version of [[Illyasviel von Einzbern]], and is initially referred to by the cast as "Black Illya" (黒イリヤ Kuro Illya).  As she also refers to herself as Illyasviel von Einzbern, she was later given the name "Kuro" (クロ), from "Black" (黒 Kuro), to differentiate her from the regular Illya. She herself later expanded on that name when she needed to have a full name and called herself "Chloe von Einzbern" (クロエ・フォン・アインツベルン, Kuroe is how the Japanese write Chloe). Throughout the series though she sticks to predominately using the name "Kuro" (クロ), and is referred to as such by herself and the rest of the cast.

Chloe is also a servant under the Archer designation in [[Fate/Grand Order]], wielding Kanshou and Bakuya with great skill, and later gains a Summer version [[Chloe von Einzbern (Swimsuit Avenger)|under the Avenger designation]].

title: illyasviel_von_einzbern
body:
A character from [[Fate/Stay Night]]. She is voiced by [[Kadowaki Mai]], and her nickname is Illya.

A young German aristocrat competing in the 5th Holy Grail War. Due to her white-blonde hair and red eyes, she is often considered an albino by fans. Her Servant is Berserker [[Heracles (fate)|]].

She appears in [[Fate/Grand Order]] as an Alter Ego Servant [[Sitonai (fate)|]], as a composite of Sitonai, Freyja, and Louhi.

Another version of her is a fifth-grade [[magical girl]] in the spinoff [[Fate/Kaleid Liner Prisma Illya]], who also appears in Fate/Grand Order as a Caster-class Servant.

title: ibuki_suika
body:
The "Little Pandemonium". Final boss of [[Touhou]]'s [[Immaterial and Missing Power]] and later a recurring playable character. 

Suika claims to be the only [[oni]] living above the ground in [[Gensokyo]] - the rest of her kind have lived underground for centuries. She is always found [[drunk]]en, carrying a bottomless [[gourd]] of [[sake]], and is an avid lover of parties. She has the power to control the density of any given object. She is explicitly based on the oni king Shuten-douji.

She is friends with [[Yakumo Yukari]], [[Hoshiguma Yuugi]] (both were once part of the "Four Devas of the Mountains") and [[Hakurei Reimu]], whose shrine also serves as her sometimes home. She and [[Ibaraki Kasen]] appear to have a slightly strained relationship, given Kasen's breaking rank with the other Gensokyo Sages, but the two remain mostly friendly to each other.

Her hair color varies between [[blonde hair|blonde]], [[brown hair|brown]], or [[orange hair|orange]] but is almost always [[very long hair|very long]] and [[low-tied long hair|tied near the bottom]] with [[sidelocks]]. Her eyes also [[yellow eyes|vary]] [[brown eyes|between]] [[orange eyes|those]] colors or [[red eyes|red]]. She wears a [[red bow]] in her [[hair bow|hair]] and a [[purple bow]] [[horn bow|on]] [[brown horns]]. Her outfit is a [[sleeveless shirt|sleeveless]] [[white shirt]], a [[red bowtie]], a [[ribbon-trimmed skirt|ribbon-trimmed]] [[purple skirt]], [[white socks]], and [[black footwear|black]] [[shoes]]. She sometimes has her [[wrist cuffs]] or normal [[cuffs]] with a [[cube]], [[orb]], and [[pyramid (geometry)|]] attached on [[chain]]s.

title: joker_(cookie)
body:
Voice of [[Mizuhashi Parsee]] in [[Cookie (Touhou)|Nabe☆]], [[Murasa Minamitsu]] in Myorenji☆, [[Kirisame Marisa]] in Viet Cong☆, and Parsee in Gyudon☆. Identifiable by her [[parted bangs]] and very pointy ears. Due to Parsee's outfit having many colors, she is put on a [b]C[/b]yan [b]B[/b]ackground compared to the more common blue or green background. Has a very husky voice that led her to play the more tomboyish roles and famous for being a bigger lesbian than [[Mars (cookie)|]]. Her dedication to voice acting as an amateur led to her being the breakout star of Nabe☆. Named herself after Joker in [[Danzai no Maria]]. 

Started out initially unpopular as Nabe☆ was a failure. She was so unpopular that her unpopularity made her popular during the Unprecedented [[Majime-kun]] Boom of 2016, later getting grouped with [[Akanuma]], [[Ryuuga (cookie)|]], and [[Yuusaku (inmu)|]]. Her unrecognizableness became her biggest joke, with others just refering to her as "Who?" (taken from Akanuma) or "That mysterious elf". Frequent jokes about her being homeless because of how unpopular she is began to spread too. A video of Joker dancing was leaked in 2017, but unlike other doxxings this ended with the doxxer being harassed for having crossed a line. During Nabe☆ she adds a [[daikon]] into the nabe, so [[Reu Daikon]] began appearing alongside her, or her in a daikon costume herself. For some reason also has been paired with [[Suzu (cookie)|]], to the point where it SZJO is now both of their main ships.
