title: awacs
body: An acronym for [b]A[/b]irborne [b]W[/b]arning [b]A[/b]nd [b]C[/b]ontrol [b]S[/b]ystem. An AWACS plane is typically a modified civilian [[jet airliner|airliner]] with extensive electronics systems and a massive [[radar dish]] mounted to the top of the plane's fuselage. Their purpose is to coordinate the activities of large numbers of military aircraft in lieu of a traditional control tower, in addition to providing quick notice of sudden battlefield changes as well as periodically providing electronic warfare support.

title: howto:tag
body:
[expand=Table of Contents]
* "Rule of Thumb":[#dtext-rule-of-thumb]
* "Minimal Tagging Criteria":[#dtext-minimal-tagging-criteria]
* "General Tags":[#dtext-general-tags]
** "Commonly Blacklisted Tags":[#dtext-blacklisted-tags]
* "Missing Information":[#dtext-missing-information]
* "Using the Related Tags Features":[#dtext-using-related-tags]
** "Related Tags":[#dtext-related-tags]
** "Related Artists":[#dtext-related-artists]
** "Related Characters":[#dtext-related-characters]
** "Related Copyrights":[#dtext-related-copyrights]
** "Find Artist":[#dtext-find-artist]
** "Favorite Tags":[#dtext-favorite-tags]
** "Beware of Limitations":[#dtext-limitations]
* "Tag Consistency and Integrity":[#dtext-tag-consistency]
** "Use Danbooru's Existing Tags":[#dtext-use-existing-tags]
* "Creating a New Tag":[#dtext-tag-creation]
* "See Also":[#dtext-see-also]
* "Further Reading":[#dtext-further-reading]
[/expand]

Tagging is the second most important job on [[danbooru (site)|Danbooru]], and should be done meticulously.

By tagging an image with [b]keywords which describe the content[/b], users are able to search for images featuring a specific character or theme. Detailed and specialized tagging is what made Danbooru become an anime-art [i]database[/i], instead of just a huge collection only good enough for casual browsing.

Users at "Member":[/wiki_pages/43574] level can be invited to become "Builder":[/wiki_pages/43574] when their prominent tagging efforts are noticed. 
([tn]See "Help:Users#Getting_Promoted":[/wiki_pages/43574] for more information.[/tn])

If you have any trouble or issue with tagging, please create a thread in the "Forum":/forum_topics to ask, or consider using an already existing tag help thread.
[quote]
[b]Existing tag help threads:[/b]

* [b]How do I tag this?[/b] (topic #12251) is for help on tagging things specifically.
* [b]Wiki Requests[/b] (topic #12858) is for questions on the definition of a tag. 
[/quote]

h4#rule_of_thumb. Rule of Thumb

[b]Tag what you see, not what you know[/b]. In other words, only tag [b]the visual and factual elements in the image[/b]. For example, images where the full moon is prominently depicted will have a [[full_moon]] tag. Ideally you should use an existing tag on Danbooru.
This means you should not tag what you know about a character. For example [[Remilia Scarlet]] is supposed to be a vampire, but don't tag every picture depicting her with the [[vampire]] tag. Only use the vampire tag if the characteristics are clearly visible. 

[b]Do not[/b] use [[tag_group:subjective|subjective tags]] (such as sexy, cute, hot, etc.). These tags are problematic because they are based on personal opinion, and different opinions can conflict. Images based on a subjective theme can be collected into a pool instead.

Examples of pools for subjective themes:

* pool #1636: Fund It!
* pool #1908: What has science done?!?

Please consult [[help:pools]] for more information on creating pools.

h4#minimal_tagging_criteria. Minimal Tagging Criteria

[b]Artist.[/b] See [[help:artists]] for more information.

[b]Character.[/b] All featured characters must be positively identified.
* See [[howto:character]]

[b]Copyright.[/b] Indicate from which series the characters came from.
* The [[original]] tag is used for art that is not based on any established works (anime, game, manga, movie).
* See [[howto:copyright]]

[b]Source.[/b] The original URL the image was taken from must be provided. If there's no URL, indicate by words from where the material came from (i.e. name of the artbook, name of doujinshi, imageboard, [[scan]] etc)

[b]Rating.[/b] Explicit material must be indicated according to [[howto:rate]].

[b]Spoilers.[/b] Some images are spoilers themselves, and must be declared with the [[spoilers]] tag.

h4#general_tags. General Tags

Describing the image in simple keywords - What objects are in the image ([[gun]], [[jacket]], etc.)? Is there a particular theme to the image (is it [[Christmas]]? Is there a [[war]]? etc.)?

Remember: There are a lot users who are not familiar with a character or a copyright, so using the following basic tags will enable those without such knowledge to recognize and search for images easily.

See the [[howto:tag checklist|Tag Checklist]] for a list of basic tags, ordered by importance.

See also: the [[list of commonly misused tags]], and our [[tag groups]], the dictionary of tags.

h6#blacklisted_tags. Commonly Blacklisted Tags

The following must be tagged upon upload to ensure users' [[help:blacklists|blacklists]] work as intended:

* [[Furry]]
* [[Guro]]
* [[Incest]]
* [[Loli]], [[Shota]] (see topic #8650)
* [[Peeing]]
* [[Rape]]
* [[Scat]] (also known as feces, shit)
* [[Spoilers]]. Repeated due to its importance.
* [[Vomit]]
* [[Yaoi]], [[Male Focus]]

h4#missing_information. Missing Information

[[Source_request]], if the source of the image is not known.

[[Tagme]]*, if contents of the image are not known. This includes items and weapons characters are seen wielding, or exotic accessories they are wearing. [b]Do not intentionally use[/b] [[tagme]] as an excuse for being too lazy to tag own uploads. 

h4#using_related_tags. Using the Related Tags Features

[quote]
[b]Note:[/b] This part of the guide only applies to the built-in tag editor on the Post Full View. If you are using DanbooruUp or any third party tools, please also consult the tools' own documentation for help.
[/quote]

Danbooru's Related Tags features are a great help at finding suitable candidates among the tens of thousands of tags already in use on Danbooru. If, for example, you are having some difficulty coming up with a new tag for the likes of that seemingly exotic accessory that character is wearing on her forearm, Related Tags may help you find the tag you have been looking for.

When you call on one of the Related Tags features, you will get a list of commonly accompanying tags for the tag that the cursor is currently on. It will also list the tags that are linked from its wiki page.

Add related tags by clicking on a tag from the lists that appear. Tags that have been added will be highlighted in blue. Clicking on a highlighted tag removes the tag from the image.

h6#related_tags. Related Tags

For the tag that your cursor is currently on, you will get a list of tags which commonly accompany it.

Consider the tag [[witch]]. Calling on Related Tags will reveal that images with [[witch]] also tend to contain [[broom]], [[ribbon]], [[witch_hat]], and [[dress]]. Owing to the fact that the black witch [[Kirisame_Marisa]], a character from [[Touhou]] is very heavily featured on Danbooru's collection, both tags will also appear on the list.

h6#related_characters. Related Characters

For the tag that your cursor is currently on, you will get only [[character:]] tags which commonly accompany it. This is intended to be used with [[copyright:]] tags. Consider the tag [[K-On!]] (full: [[copyright:K-On!]]). The list for [[K-On!]] will mostly feature names of characters from [[K-On!]].

Beware that characters from other copyrights may creep up into this list. This happens because there is a considerable number of [[crossover]] [[K-On!]] art. Verify this with this search {{K-On! crossover}}. 

h6#related_copyrights. Related Copyrights

For the tag that your cursor is currently on, you will get only [[copyright:]] tags that commonly accompany it. This is intended to be used with [[character:]] tags. Consider the infamous miko with detached sleeves, [[Hakurei_Reimu]]. Calling on related copyrights will list [[Touhou]] related copyrights, and crossovers featuring [[Touhou]] characters.

h6#favorite_tags. Favorite Tags

This is a list of tags which have been entered into your [b]Uploaded Tags[/b] list in you Settings screen under your [b]My Account[/b] control panel.

h6#limitations. Beware of Limitations

The Related Tags lists are arranged alphabetically, instead of by relevance, or by number of posts. This may cause complete confusion to taggers who are completely new to the copyright or characters featured on the image they have just uploaded.

For this reason, it is always advisable to research copyrights and the associated characters before tagging.

h4#tag-consistency. Tag Consistency and Integrity

Please double-check your tags on the left side of the screen after applying them. If you have any tags with a total count of 1, a new tag has been created. Often, tag creation on Danbooru is not necessary. If this happens, please check that your tags have been correctly spelled.

To ensure that your tags are correctly spelled, it is best to pick your tags from the Related Tags lists, as doing this automatically enters the tags for you.

h6#use_existing_tags. Use Danbooru's Existing Tags

Please use Danbooru's existing tags whenever possible, but do create a new tag if you are sure that it is not covered by existing tags or pools. If you aren't sure about which tag to use, don't be afraid to ask on the forums. Danbooru most often uses the original language's title when naming copyrights and characters, so always double check. See [[howto:copyright]] and [[howto:romanize]] for details.

h4#tag_creation. Creating a New Tag

Only ASCII characters are permitted in tag names. Tags must be romanized if they're coming from Japanese or another language that uses non-ASCII characters. See [[howto:romanize]] for details.

h6. Name restrictions

Tag names carry several restrictions, either for technical reasons or simplicity:
* Tags cannot contain non-ASCII characters. This includes Japanese letters. Replace them with their appropriate [[howto:romanize|romanization]] if necessary.
* Tags cannot contain asterisks. They are used as a wildcard in searches.
* Tags cannot contain spaces. Replace them with underscores instead, as spaces are used to delimit tags.
* Tags cannot contain commas.
* Tags cannot end with an underscore.
* Tags cannot contain consecutive underscores.
* Tags cannot contain unprintable characters.
* Tags cannot exceed 170 characters in length.

h6. Tag types

* [b]Artist[/b] names carry the prefix ''artist:'' or ''art:''
* [b]Character[/b] names carry the prefix ''character:'' or ''char:''
* [b]Copyright[/b] titles carry the prefix ''copyright:'' or ''copy:''
* [b]Meta[/b] tags carry the prefix ''meta:''
* [b]General[/b] tags are normally not prefixed at all, because all tags without a prefix are by default automatically assumed to be ''general:'' or ''gen:''

If you create a tag with the wrong type, or notice a tag with an incorrect type, you can edit the post and add the correct prefix to the tag in order to change its type. This can only be done for existing tags if their post count is lower than a certain amount depending on user level, the specific thresholds are documented in [[help:users]].

h6. Naming a tag
[b]Use singular nouns.[/b] This especially concerns tags about objects which appear multiple times in an image. Under all circumstances, use the [b]singular[/b] for the object. If an image contains a bin full of [[wispberries]], tag it [[wispberry]]. This greatly simplifies searching and tagging.

[b]Resolving Ambiguities with Qualifiers.[/b] If the tag you are going to use had already been taken up for another purpose (other character with the same name, character with the same name as an object, character and series have the same name, etc.), add a qualifier between () to distinguish them.

For example Black Rock Shooter is both the OVA name and the female protagonist's name.

* [[Black_Rock_Shooter]] is used for the copyright.
* [[Black_Rock_Shooter_(character)]] is used to indicate the female protagonist.

See [[help:qualifiers]] for further reading.

[b]New Character Tags.[/b] Always use the character's full name in your tags. Name order should appear the same as in the original materials. Commonly:
* SurName_FirstName for Asians. Example: [[Shameimaru_Aya]], where Shameimaru is her surname.
* FirstName_SurName for Westerners, and most other ethnicities. Example: [[Ken_Masters]].

h4#see_also. See Also

* [[howto:tag_checklist|Tagging Checklist]]
* [[Tag_groups|Tag Groups]]

h4#further_reading. Further Reading

* "Danbooru Legacy Help on Tags":/help/tags (Note: Obsolete, for reference purposes only)

[[howto:contribute|Return to the Contributor Guide]]
[[help:toc|Return to the Table of Contents]]
[[help:home|Return to the Wiki Help Home Page]]

title: help:upload
body:
[expand=Table of Contents]
* "Danbooru Upload Guidelines":[#dtext-upload-guidelines]
* "Uploading":[#dtext-uploading]
** "Minimal Tagging Criteria":[#dtext-minimal-tagging-criteria]
** "Make Use of Comments, Discord and the Forum":[#dtext-make-use-of-comments-and-the-forum]
** "Check for Duplicates":[#dtext-check-for-duplicates]
* "See Also":[#dtext-see-also]
[/expand]

h4#upload-guidelines. Danbooru Upload Guidelines

Thank you for donating your spare time to help the Danbooru collection grow. While we need a constant supply of new images to keep our collection fresh and up to date, we must make it clear that Danbooru has stricter quality standards compared to most galleries of its kind.

Here are a couple of things to know before you begin:

h5. Read the [[help:upload rules|Upload Rules]] before proceeding

The upload rules describe what is and isn't allowed. In particular:

* Fully [[ai-generated]] works and [[paid reward]]s are forbidden.
* Some types of posts, like [[cosplay photo]]s, [[furry]] artwork, and extreme fetish content are considered borderline and should be uploaded sparingly.

Please read the upload rules in full before proceeding.

h5#subjective. Danbooru is Subjective

Please keep in mind that not everything you upload may be approved. Danbooru judges posts based on quality, which is a highly subjective measure. While there's no way to know for sure whether a post will be approved, uploaders can gauge a rough idea of what the standards are by looking at preexisting approved posts. Search {{status:active approver:any}} to find posts that have gone through and passed approval.

Generally, posts with [[bad anatomy]] or a lot of [[JPEG artifacts]], or very [[lowres|low resolution]] will have a hard time getting approved, while competently drawn images will be approved fairly quickly. If you're not sure whether an image meets our standards, you can try asking in the [official Discord server](https://discord.gg/danbooru).

Don't take it personally if a few of your uploads are deleted - we've all been there at some point. If you think your posts deserve a second look, you can appeal them. See the [[howto:appeal]] page for more information.

h4#uploading. Uploading

To upload a post, simply either paste the link into the "upload page":[/uploads/new], use the "bookmarklet":[/static/bookmarklet], or the "web extension":[https://github.com/danbooru/upload-to-danbooru]. Many of the most popular art sites are supported natively by Danbooru, so all it takes is pasting a link into the upload page. "See here":/static/bookmarklet for a list of supported sites.

Try not to upload images from sources that aren't from the original artist or a [[second-party source]] (official accounts for a game or anime in case of [[official art]], or a commissioner, etc), and always look for an [[help:image source|original source]] whenever possible. Sites such as 4chan, Reddit, or Facebook are not ideal places to source your image, unless the artist posted their art there or has long deleted their original post.

Try to avoid picking files directly from your device, as doing this means you won't benefit from the source and artist tag autofilling that Danbooru performs. Exceptions to this are if the original post by the artist is no longer available (in which case, remember to tag [[bad id]]) or if you're uploading your own artwork (please specify so by tagging [[self-upload]]).

h5#minimal_tagging_criteria. Minimal Tagging Criteria

Comprehensive tagging is the essence of Danbooru, [[unlimited blade works (reality marble)|its body and its blood]]. The basic expectations for tagging are as follows:

* Artists must be credited.
** If you uploaded by pasting a link, Danbooru should autofill this data for you, assuming the artist is in our database.
** If not, read [[help:artists]] for information on creating an entry.
** If all else fails, or the artist is unidentifiable by any conventional means (common with [[official art]]), tag [[artist request]].
* Copyrights which a character is from must be identified.
** Place a [[copyright request]] if you cannot surely identify it.
* Characters must be identified.
** Use the [[original]] tag if it's an original character.
*** Some recurring [[original]] characters may have character tags of their own. They may be listed on the artist's wiki page, which you can access through the question mark symbol next to the artist's tag.
** Place a [[character request]] if you aren't sure where a character comes from.
* All posts should be tagged to at least Level 1 per the [[howto:tag checklist]].
** If you are not sure if an image is tagged completely enough, always place a [[tagme]] tag, and another contributor will review your tags, adding and making corrections as necessary. 
** Do not frequently use [[tagme]] as an excuse for being too lazy to tag own uploads. Neglecting tagging is considered a violation of the rules and may lead to action being taken against your account if done repeatedly.

For Tagging Guidelines in greater detail, please see [[howto:tag]] and [[howto:tag_checklist]].

h5#make_use_of_comments_and_the_forum. Make Use of Comments, Discord and the Forum

Most of the time, a cursory trip to Google will help you accomplish most things such as finding out which copyright a character comes from. If you have an issue that where Google research just wouldn't do, please [[help:comments|leave a comment]] on the image about the issue you want to clarify, or ask in the "Official Discord":https://discord.gg/danbooru or in the forums.

h5#check_for_duplicates. Check for Duplicates

Be sure that your post has not been uploaded by someone else. When uploading an image that the system has deemed to be a likely duplicate, a [b]Duplicate[/b] badge will appear below the image.

If your image has already been uploaded, only upload if you have a higher quality copy. Once you have uploaded your higher quality copy, set all existing copies of the image as child posts of your copy.
Bigger size doesn't necessarily mean better quality, unless the filesizes vastly differ. For example, if one image is 800 kb and another is 840 kb, it's very likely they'll be [[duplicate]]s. Always check the images closely before uploading if you're unsure.

For more information on setting Parent and Child Posts, refer to the chapter on [[help:post_relationships|Managing Parent and Child Posts]] in the Contributor's Guide.

h4#see_also. See also

* [[about:mod_queue|Moderation Queue]]
* [[howto:appeal|Deletion Appeals]]
* [[help:upload_rules|Upload Rules]]


[[howto:contribute|Return to the Contributor Guide]]
[[help:toc|Return to the Table of Contents]]
[[help:home|Return to the Wiki Help Home Page]]

title: marichka
body:
Marichka (more commonly known as Azov-chan) is a female character designed as the anthropomorphic representation of the [[Azov Battalion]], first appearing in late 2021 amidst rising tensions, and went viral following the start of the [[russo-ukrainian war|2022 Russian invasion of Ukraine]]. Her real name is "Maria".

Following the war, several characters were created in her wake, representing various Azov-friendly factions within Ukraine and its army, broadly lumped together into the 'Mariverse'. These characters include [[Kraken (japanon)|]], [[Eva (kavunyak)|]], [[Nika (usergore)|]], [[Olesya (miaz)|]], [[Zoriana]], [[Paulinka (japanon)|]], [[Lera (sighttobehold)|]], [[Stepan (number-seventeen)|]], [[Levchenko Ahapiia Oleksandrivna]], [[Khrystyna Karpenko]], [[Olena Bozhuk]], [[Myroslava Bozhuk]], [[Kupalinka]], [[Cossack (polish anon)|]], [[Emilia Plyaterska]], [[Hanna Kovalchuk]], [[Shefika (usergore)|]], and [[Kenneth del Duca]]. 

h4. External links

* "Know Your Meme: Azov-Chan / Marichka":https://knowyourmeme.com/memes/azov-chan-marichka
* "Marichka Wiki (English)":https://marichka.fandom.com/wiki/Marichka_Wiki

title: mizuhashi_parsee
body:
The "Jealousy Beneath the Crust of the Earth".

Stage 2 boss of [[Touhou]]'s [[Subterranean Animism]] and a side character in [[Foul Detective Satori]]. A Persian "Hashihime":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hashihime that has the ability to manipulate jealousy. She lives in the [[bridge]] leading to the underworld, often attempting to drive away anyone who attempts to cross it and losing herself in a jealous rage whenever she fails. Parsee also demonstrates the ability to have a [[clone|copy of herself]] through her spell cards. Often paired with [[Hoshiguma Yuugi]] or [[Kurodani Yamame]] in fanworks due to their stages being next to each other, but also [[Kagiyama Hina]] due to both being stage 2 bosses who deal with negative emotions. 

Her appearance is very inconsistent and confusing, leading artists to draw her in a variety of ways. She usually has [[short hair|short]] [[blonde hair]] with a [[half updo]] or a [[half up braid]], [[green eyes]], [[pointy ears]]. Her outfit is a [[white scarf]], and then a [[short sleeves|short-sleeved]] [[brown shirt]] over a [[black dress]] but sometimes a separate [[black shirt|black]] [[undershirt]] and [[black skirt|skirt]], a [[white sash]], [[arm warmers]], [[loose socks|loose]] [[white socks]], and [[black footwear|black]] [[mary janes]].

title: assault_rifle
body:
An infantry [[rifle]] designed for combat, with selective fire capability. The German [[StG44]] was the very first mass-produced assault rifle ever designed and introduced in battle.

In the strictest of definitions for a [[gun|firearm]] to be considered an assault rifle, it must at least follow these characteristics:
* It must be an individual weapon with provision to fire from the shoulder (i.e. a buttstock);
* It must be capable of selective fire (semi and full auto, some models may feature burst fire mode);
* It must have an [[rifle cartridge|intermediate-power cartridge]], which has more power and velocity than a pistol round but less than a standard full-power ones (i.e. 5.56×45mm NATO);
* Its [[ammunition]] must be supplied from a detachable box [[magazine (weapon)|]].

title: honoka_(doa)
body:
A high school student and martial artist who made her debut in the 2015 title [[Dead or Alive 5]].

She has [[pink eyes]] and [[short hair|short]] to [[medium hair|medium length]] [[pink hair]] stylized with a [[one side up]] & [[bangs]]. Usually wears a [[skull hair ornament]]. Her [[school uniform]] consists of a [[white shirt|white]] [[collared shirt]], [[blazer]], [[red necktie]], [[single glove|single]] [[black gloves|black glove]], [[plaid skirt|plaid]] [[pleated skirt]], [[white thighhighs]], and [[black footwear|black]] [[loafers]]. She has the [[large breasts|largest breast size]] out of all DOA characters, not counting [[Nicole 458]].

Her overall appearance and hairstyle may be based on the [[Honoka Sisters]] from [[Sidonia no Kishi]], but her side ponytail and hair ornament are a reference to [[Kosaka Honoka]] from [[Love Live!]].

In December 2020, she received the skin [[Honoka (Summer Angel on the Shore) (DoA)|]] as part of a collab with [[Azur Lane]].

title: decarabian_(genshin_impact)
body:
A character from [[Genshin Impact]]. Also known as the "God of Storms" or "Lord of the Tower", he was a god from around 2600 years before the events of the game who founded and ruled Old Mondstadt.

At an unknown point in time, Decarabian founded Old Mondstadt, which at it's peak, spread through Brightcrown Mountains and Windwail Highland with the capital city in the area now known as Stormterror's Lair. During the Archon War, conflict grew between him and [[Andrius (genshin impact)|Boreas]], starting the era known as the "Age of Kings". Using his power, Boreas transformed the land around Mondstadt into a frozen wasteland, leading to Decarabian surrounding the capital city with a wind barrier, barring both exit and entry.

In his eyes, he gave his people shelter from the bitter cold and believed they loved him as he did them. However, to his people, he was a cruel and selfish ruler who locked them in. As frustration over Decarabian's rule grew, it would lead to a rebellion which was led by the [[Nameless Bard (genshin impact)|]], a [[Barbatos (genshin impact)|wind spirit]], Decarabian's former lover [[Amos (genshin impact)|]], a knight (possibly [[Gunnhildr (genshin impact)|]]) and a [[red-haired warrior (genshin impact)|]] (possibly an ancestor to [[Diluc (genshin impact)|]]). They would eventually emerge victorious as Decarabian was finally slain. Decarabian's death, along with Boreas choosing to pass on, allowed Barbatos to ascend to godhood and become the Anemo Archon.

He is named after Decarabia, the 69th demon from the [[Ars Goetia]].

h4. See also

* [[List of Genshin Impact characters]]

* "Genshin Impact Wiki: Decarabian":https://genshin-impact.fandom.com/wiki/Decarabian

title: hwang_mi-ae
body:
Hwang Mi-ae is the female protagonist of the webcomic [i][[After School Lessons for Unripe Apples]][/i]. She is a third year student of Baekje Middle School and former childhood friends with the male lead, [[Kim Cheol]]. She's energetic with a cheerful and kind personality, though it is often pointed out that she is absent-minded and childish in many regards. She is deeply considerate of her peers and quick to defend her friends even if it will lead to misunderstandings among them.

Her appearance is most noticeable due to her short stature, especially in comparison with her male peers with her being seen as a child next to Cheol, as well as her [[thick eyebrows]]. Her hair changes often throughout the story, but she is most often seen with a [[bob cut]] as her school's dress code requires girls and boys alike to have short hair.

Real-life Hungarian racehorse from the late 19th century, she has by far the longest undefeated race record of any racehorse, being undefeated in all of her 54 races (second best record is 25 races by [[Black Caviar (racehorse)|]]).

She was a chestnut (or liver chestnut) mare with no markings, often described as ugly and noted to have a quirky personality. She was also something of a living legend figure, thus much of her life story should be taken with a grain of salt.

Although she had few foals, her mare-line survives in modern times through both of her surviving fillies. One of the most notable modern day descendant of hers is [[Camelot (racehorse)|]], who challenged the British Triple Crown.

title: chan_agi
body:
A fictional female character from the [[Gundam]] [[mecha|mechaverse]]. She appears in [[Char's Counterattack]] from 1988.

[b]Chan Agi[/b] is a [i]Londo Bell[/i] Fleet [[Earth Federation]] officer and [[military]] assistant to [[Amuro Ray]].

[spoilers]During the final space battle of the film she pilots a damaged [[Re-GZ]] and accidentaly destroys [[Quess Paraya]] in her [[Alpha Azieru]] while trying to protect [[Hathaway Noa]]. Then Chan is herself killed by an enraged Hathaway in a [[Jegan]]. However, it is implied that her spirit survives in the portable "T" shaped [[psycho frame]] unit she had in her belt.[/spoilers]

[spoilers]Later the glowing device is shown floating in space meaning her ghost somehow helped Amuro stop Axis from falling into Earth.[/spoilers]

title: ear_picking

title: obijime
body:
[b]Obijime[/b] is a small decorative string tied around the [[obi]], used only in women's [[kimono]].

It's about 150 cm (4.9 ft) long and is tied around the obi and through the knot, and which doubles as decoration. It can be a woven [[string]], or be constructed as a narrow sewn tube of fabric. There are both flat and round obijime. They often have [[tassel]]s at both ends and are made from [[silk]], [[satin]], brocade or viscose. A cord-like or a padded tube obijime is considered more festive and ceremonial than a flat one.

h4. See also
* [[obiage]]
* [[obidome]]
* [[Japanese clothes]]

title: ammunition_belt
body:
A belt of [[ammunition]] as feeding device for belt-fed [[gun|firearms]]. Commonly [[machine gun]], [[minigun]] or [[Gatling gun]].

The [[rifle cartridge|cartridges]] are held in chains of looped metal links which can be connected to form belts of any length. It may disintegrate after firing or not. These disposable links are discarded (along with the empty [[shell casing]]s) upon firing. 

Not to be confused with a [[bandolier]], which is a belt or sash containing cartridges worn on a person's chest, or an [[ammunition pouch]], which is a [[pouch]] for holding ammunition that may be worn around the waist.

title: m1_abrams
body:
The M1 Abrams is the current main battle [[tank]] of the United States Army. Entering service in 1980, it replaced the Vietnam-era M60 Patton. It uses composite armor, and its distinctive slab-sided turret, with its sloping panels, is a consequence of this. Its gas turbine engine resides in a raised afterdeck.

The Abrams was originally armed with a 105mm [[cannon]], subsequently upgraded to 120mm. Other weapons includes a roof-mounted .50 caliber M2 machine gun and 2 7.62mm [[machine gun|machine guns]]. These may be supplanted by remotely-controlled weapon stations using a Mk. 19 automatic grenade launcher or an M134 [[gatling gun|Minigun]].

It is the vehicular motif of the [[Decepticon]] [[Brawl (transformers)|]] in the [[Transformers]] live-action films.

h4. External links

* "Wikipedia: M1 Abrams":http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/M1_Abrams

title: tank
body:
An armored, [[caterpillar tracks|tracked]] [[military vehicle]] with a single [[cannon]] (some tanks may have mounted [[machine gun]]s or more than one cannon). Its heavy armor protects  the crew from enemy fire while the tracks let it traverse difficult terrain or obstacles.

For tagging purposes this tag may also be used on any tank-like [[motor vehicle|vehicle]], whether real or fictional. This may include things such as tank destroyers (ex: [[Sturmgeschutz III]]), [[self-propelled artillery]] (ex: [[M109 Howitzer]]), rocket artillery, and the like.

For the container type tank, use the tag: [[tank (container)]]. Do not confuse with [[tank top]], which refers to a type of shirt.

h4. Examples

* !post #7558772: Modern Main Battle Tank (MBT) ([[M1 Abrams]])
* !post #8075834: [[Turretless Tank|Turretless]] [[Tank Destroyer]] ([[Sturmgeschutz III]])
* !post #2641172: Tracked [[Self-propelled Artillery]] ([[M109 Howitzer]])

title: jinshi_(kusuriya_no_hitorigoto)
body:
Jinshi is the male lead of the series [[Kusuriya no Hitorigoto]].  Known as the beautiful eunuch of the rear palace, in-universe he is officially stated to be 23 at the start of the series.  Jinshi is described as possessing the beauty of a nymph that transcends gender and is usually depicted with [[long_hair|long]] [[black_hair|black]] to [[purple hair]], commonly worn with a [[bun_cover|covered]] [[hair bun]] in the back.[spoilers] After the events of volume 4, his face was marred with a [[scar_on_cheek|scar running down the side of his cheek]][/spoilers].

Jinshi officially is a eunuch who manages the Imperial harem in the rear palace.  Tasked with taking care of, monitoring, and evaluating the consorts who live within the rear palace's walls.  He is frequently accompanied by his attendant [[Gaoshun_(kusuriya_no_hitorigoto)|]].  He first formally meets [[Maomao_(kusuriya_no_hitorigoto)|]] when he took up the task of finding out the identity of the unknown benefactor who had left a note at high consort [[Gyokuyou_(kusuriya_no_hitorigoto)|]]'s palace that saved the life of her daughter.  He ends up developing an interest in her due to a mix of her intelligence, knowledge, and how she frequently is more likely to show him contempt instead of swooning over him like most people.

h4. Appearance

* !asset #19757497: Anime

title: kusuriya_no_hitorigoto
body:
Kusuriya no Hitorigoto (English title: The Apothecary Diaries) is a series of light novels by Hyuuga Natsu and illustrated by [[Shino Touko]]. It originally started as a web novel in 2011, but its first volume was picked up by Ray Books in 2012 and subsequently published by Hero Bunkoban. There are two manga adaptations; the former (Kusuriya no Hitorigoto) by [[Nekokurage_(Gen'eikai_Tsuushin)|Nekokurage]] in Big Gangan, and latter (Kusuriya no Hitorigoto: Maomao no Koukyuu Nazotoki Techou) by [[Kurata Minoji]] in Sunday Gene-X. A Historical Fantasy, it is set in a Chinese inspired land.

title: death_flag
body:
[i](Shibou Furagu)[/i]

A sign to the audience that a character is about to [[death|die]], and/or otherwise foreshadowing an imminent [[bad end]].

A death flag is usually raised by a character saying or doing something that can be seen as tempting fate.  Examples include: Doing something that he or she has been warned, sometimes repeatedly, could be fatal; an unrequited relationship suddenly and finally being requited, especially if it comes out of the blue; a promise to return just before leaving on a journey of uncertain length; and so on.

h4. See also

* pool #17266 - Tempting Fate

title: durin_(real)_(genshin_impact)
body:
A character from [[Genshin Impact]], he was a [[dragon]] created by the alchemist [[Rhinedottir (genshin impact)|]] and she classified him as "Humus". She considered him as one of her masterpieces along with [[Albedo (genshin impact)|]].

Around 500 years ago, he invaded Mondstadt during the Cataclysm and caused massive devastation. With no one capable of defending the nation, [[Barbatos (genshin impact)|]] was awoken to the pleas of his people and fought against him together with [[Dvalin (genshin impact)|]]. 

Durin was eventually killed and sent plummeting to an area in Dragonspine now known as Wyrmrest Valley where his remains lie to this day. His corpse spread his life energy throughout the valley and caused the formation of [[Crimson Agate (genshin impact)|]] and Scarlet Quartz. Durin's blood was very toxic and contained power from the Abyss. After the battle, Dvalin was put into a deep sleep in Decarabian's Tower for ingesting his blood and was one of the catalysts to Dvalin becoming "Stormterror".

He is often depicted in canon as a black skeletal dragon with [[glowing eyes|glowing]] [[red eyes]].

Not to be confused with [[Mini Durin (genshin impact)|]] who appears as either a [[Mini Durin (Dragon) (Genshin Impact)|small dragon]] or a [[Mini Durin (Human) (Genshin Impact)|dragon boy]]. He is <spoiler>an alternate counterpart created by the Hexenzirkel who was later granted a human form by Albedo.</spoiler>

He is named after the [[dwarf]] Durinn from [[Norse Mythology]].

h4. See also

* [[Mini Durin (genshin impact)|]]
* [[List of Genshin Impact characters]]

h4. External links

* "Genshin Impact Wiki: Durin":https://genshin-impact.fandom.com/wiki/Durin

title: andrius_(genshin_impact)
body:
A character from [[Genshin Impact]]. Also known as "Boreas", he was a god in Mondstadt and is currently the Wolf of the North of Mondstadt's Four Winds.

At an unknown point in time, an unknown ancient god gave Boread his powers, putting him on the level of a god. During the Archon War, conflict grew between him and [[Decarabian (genshin impact)|]], with Boreas transforming the land around Mondstadt into a frozen wasteland, leading to Decarabian surrounding his capital city with a wind barrier, barring both exit and entry. This started the era known as the "Age of Kings" and Mondstadt was consumed by ice and snow.

Sometime later during the Archon War, Boreas decided he was unworthy of becoming the Archon and chose to pass on. Boreas' passing, along with Decarabian's death, allowed [[Barbatos (genshin impact)|]] to ascend to godhood and become the Anemo Archon. After his death, part of his spirit took on his current form and sometime after [[Vennessa (genshin impact)|]]'s rebellion roughly 1000 years ago, Boreas became one of the Four Winds. Eventually, he settled in Wolvendom and became the leader of a wolf pack, taking in [[Razor (genshin impact)|]] shortly before the events of the game.

He is depicted as a large, blue and white [[wolf]] with [[glowing eyes|glowing]] [[blue eyes]].

Voiced by Jacob Craner in English and Kusunoki Taiten in Japanese.

He is named after Boreas, the God of the North Wind and Storms in [[Greek Mythology]] and his name Andrius is likely named after Andrealphus, the 65th demon from the [[Ars Goetia]].

h4. Appearance

* !post #8972999

title: barbatos_(genshin_impact)
body:
A character from [[Genshin Impact]], he is the God of Freedom and the Anemo Archon, presiding over Mondstadt. He loves freedom and refuses to take direct control of his nation, preferring to wander the world as [[Venti (genshin impact)|]] the [[bard]].

Barbatos was once a mere elemental [[spirit]] among the Thousand Winds with no divine power. At some point, he encountered [[Istaroth (genshin impact)|]] at the Thousand Winds Temple, where she gave him a fragment of her power and authority. During the Archon War, he began amassing power due to the Gunnhildr Clan worshipping him and eventually participated in the rebellion against [[Decarabian (genshin impact)|]], alongside the [[Nameless Bard (genshin impact)|]], [[Amos (genshin impact)|]], a knight (possibly [[Gunnhildr (genshin impact)|]]) and a [[red-haired warrior (genshin impact)|]] (possibly an ancestor to [[Diluc (genshin impact)|]]).

Due to [[Andrius (genshin impact)|Boreas]] deciding he was unworthy of being the Archon and choosing to pass on and Decarabian's death at the hands of his people, Barbatos ascended to godhood and became the Anemo Archon. From there, he took his people to Cider Lake, building the new [[Mondstadt City]] and drastically changed the terrain, flattening [[cliff]]s and [[mountain]]s with storms and brought in monsoons that changed Mondstadt from a snowy wasteland to a lush and fertile land.

He is depicted as a small [[spirit]] wearing a [[white cloak|white]] [[hooded cloak]].

Barbatos is [[Venti (genshin impact)|]]'s original form. This tag is specifically for his wind spirit form. Do not tag Venti's human form as Barbatos.

He is named after Barbatos, a duke of [[hell]] and the 8th demon from the [[Ars Goetia]].

h4. Appearance

* !post #5679475

h4. See also

* [[List of Genshin Impact characters]]

title: ah-1_cobra
body:
An [[attack helicopter|attack]] [[helicopter]] that combined the proven twin-bladed rotor, engine, and drive train of Bell's [[UH-1 Iroquois]] with a new slimline fuselage. It came in two main variants, the single-engine HueyCobra and the twin-engined SeaCobra (and later SuperCobra), the latter having a wider engine compartment. The AH-1 had a crew of two in tandem, with the gunner seated in front and pilot in the back. 

Fixed armament included a chin-mounted turret armed with either [[machine gun|machine guns]], grenade projectors, or a single 20mm multibarrel [[cannon]]. Stub wings on either side of the fuselage could carry additional armament, such as [[rocket|rockets]] and TOW anti-tank [[missile|missiles]].

h4. External links

* Wikipedia: "Bell AH-1":http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/AH-1
* Youtube: "Cobra Attack Helicopter":http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=UvFeyslhWRo

title: dog_(shiba_inu)_(kemono_friends)
body:
A [i][[Kemono Friends]][/i] character. She is one of many "Friends" in Japari Park.

The dog ([i]Canis lupus familliaris[/i]) needs little introduction. As suggested from their trinomal name, it is the domesticated form of the [[grey_wolf_(kemono_friends)|Grey Wolf]], having been so since the beginning of human civilization. Thanks to aggressive selective breeding and a very malleable genome, it has by far the widest phenotypic range of all domestic animals, ranging from the tiny Chihuahua (smaller to comparable to the Fennec fox, the smallest canid species) to the large mastiffs like the Great Dane (larger than actual grey wolves, whom also happen to be the largest canids). While it is considered a subspecies of wolf, their direct ancestors are long extinct and as a result, dogs are not closely related to extant wolves.

Dog (the Friend) is based on the [[Shiba Inu]], the archetypical pet dog in Japan. For this reason, she is often conflated with the [[Doge]] meme.

h4. See also
* [[Dog (Mixed Breed) (kemono friends)|]]

title: yuki_miku
body:
A winter-themed version of [[Hatsune Miku]] used for the annual SNOW MIKU event running concurrently with the [[Sapporo (city)|]] Snow Festival. There are [[snowflakes]] printed into her hair, and she wears an ice-blue outfit with parts done in glimmering silver. Her partner is a small white [[rabbit]] named [[Rabbit Yukine]].

Since 2012, there is a yearly contest to decide which fan-submitted design will be used as the official Yuki Miku of that year, the winner of which also gets their design turned into a Petite [[Nendoroid]] by [[Goodsmile Company]].

h4. Appearance

* !post #6957176: Successive Yuki Miku as of 2024; from bottom-to-top, left-to-right.

h4. Versions

* [[yuki miku (2010)|2010]] - Hatsune Miku's usual outfit colored to blue, white, and silver. 
* [[yuki miku (2011)|2011]] - Same outfit as the 2010 version, but given [[earmuffs]], a white [[scarf]], and white [[mittens]]. Now used as the default Yuki Miku.
* [[yuki miku (2012)|2012]] - "Fluffy Coat version" (ふわふわコートVer.): Wears a blue ribbon [[hairband]] and a coat with white [[fur trim]]. Has [[fur-trimmed boots]] to match.
* [[yuki miku (2013)|2013]] - "Strawberry White Dress version" (いちご白無垢Ver.): Wears a white kimono and [[uchikake]].
* [[yuki miku (2014)|2014]] - "Magical Snow version": Wears a [[witch hat]], a blue [[cape]], and wields a [[staff]].
* [[yuki miku (2015)|2015]] - "Snow Bell version": has a plant motif, wears a white [[bubble skirt]] and [[capelet]].
* [[yuki miku (2016)|2016]] - "Snow Owl version": Wears an owl-shaped [[hat]] and sports gear.
* [[yuki miku (2017)|2017]] - "Twinkle Snow version": Wields a [[wand]] and wears a sleeveless blue [[dress]].
* [[yuki miku (2018)|2018]] - "Crane Priestess version" (タンチョウ巫女Ver.): Has a crane-themed [[miko]] outfit with [[striped_legwear|striped]] [[thighhighs]].
* [[yuki miku (2019)|2019]] - "Princess version": Wields a [[scepter]] and wears a green and white [[frilled dress]], with a crystal [[tiara]], [[detached collar]], and equally as [[detached sleeves|detached]] [[juliet sleeves]].
* [[yuki miku (2020)|2020]] - "Snow Parade version": A [[band uniform]] motif with a [[french horn]], [[epaulettes]] that have a [[fringe trim]], and [[hat feather]].
* [[yuki miku (2021)|2021]] - "Glowing Snow version": A choir outfit with a clock motif featuring a [[clock print]] [[beret]] and [[white dress]].
* [[yuki miku (2022)|2022]] - "Grand Voyage version": A naval captain outfit with a crab motif featuring red [[hair ribbon]] that resemble crab claws and a [[fur-trimmed coat]].
* [[yuki miku (2023)|2023]] - "Serene Winter version": A pink and blue pastel palette [[kimono]] with a daybreak motif. She wields a [[giant brush]].
* [[yuki miku (2024)|2024]] - "Winter Feast version": A traditional [[Japanese clothes|Japanese outfit]] with a [[soup curry]] motif.
* [[yuki miku (2025)|2025]] - "Crystal Snow version": Carries an [[icicle]] [[wand]] and wears various winter-themed accessories, including [[icicle]], [[snowball]], and [[crystal|ice crystal]] [[hair ornament]]s.
* [[yuki miku (2026)|2026]] - "Sweet Snow version": Western-style dress with apron. Her hair is adorned with [[musical_note-themed_food|musical note-themed sweets]] and she wears a beret with a [[strawberry swiss roll]].

h4. See also

* [[Sakura Miku]] (spring)
* [[Aki Miku]] (autumn)
* [[Racing Miku]]
* [[List of Vocaloid derivatives]]

h4. External links

* "Official SNOW MIKU site":[http://snowmiku.com/]

title: mehve
body:
A one-person [[glider]] from [[Kaze no Tani no Nausicaa]]. Of flying wing configuration, it is powered by a single engine buried in its midsection and has skid landing gear. The manga version has small tip-dragger-type rudders at the end of the wing fairings; the movie version lacks these.

'"Mehve" is the German word "Moewe", which means "seagull" in English.' [2]

title: chen
body:
The "Black Cat of Bad Omens". Stage 2 midboss and boss, as well as Extra Stage midboss of [[Touhou]]'s [[Perfect Cherry Blossom]].

She is the [[cat girl|nekomata]] shikigami of [[Yakumo Ran]] (who is herself the shikigami of [[Yakumo Yukari]]). Despite her knowledge of black magic, Chen is rather weak by herself, only gaining a massive increase in power in the presence of her master. She is also weakened by water. Like Ran, Chen is actually the shikigami spirit possessing the nekomata, although she appears to have only a partial hold on her host and doesn't suppress the host's personality, resulting in Chen as a character being a symbiosis between the two.

Fanworks frequently portray her as a daughter figure to Ran, often exuding a level of cuteness that often gives her [[excessive nosebleed|epic nosebleeds]]. She is also considered an honorary member of [[Team 9 (touhou)|]] in some fanwork circles. She appears to have befriended [[Kaenbyou Rin]] in [[Foul Detective Satori]], who has passed on her habit of finding and retrieving dead bodies.

h4. Appearance

A large species of predominately carnivorous ocean-dwelling cartilaginous fish belonging to the clade [b]Selachii[/b]. Most have sharp teeth, are able to smell blood in the water from a far distance, and detect electrical currents.

body:
[b]Pleasure Prison Csejte[br]The Adventure of Singing Pumpkin Castle ~Mad Party 2015~[/b]
[quote]Trick or Torture! All you pumpkins around the world, are you watching?

I will hold a special concert for all you lonely pumpkins!
We'll have surprises all night on a special stage made just for this occasion - Alluring Castle Csetje!

All the staff here will welcome you every night with smiles, so please come play with me every day and every night, all right? ♥
Or else, I'm just going to eat cake by myself.

What? You're asking about the cute girl with the lovely voice? Well then, you'll have to find out when you get here!

title: shinpi_no_kuni_no_oniland!!
body:
[b]Northern Amusement Park ONI♡LAND[br]The Land of Mystique, ONILAND!! ~The Great Oni and the Kamuy's Gold~[/b]
[quote]A new Halloween story is about to begin...

The yearly Halloween Rayshift takes you to...a snow-covered land?!
Glittering snowflakes dance in the air, stands stuffed with delicious foods line the streets, dazzling performances run night and day, and of course everyone is smiling!
This place is an eternal paradise brimming with hopes and dreams...an amusement park where oni and pumpkins intertwine.
The gates of "The Land of Mystique, ONILAND!! ~The Great Oni and the Kamuy's Gold~" are now open![/quote]

A limited time [[Halloween]] event in [[Fate/Grand Order]], released on the Japanese server on October 24, 2018 and on the NA server on October 19, 2020. [[Shuten Douji (Halloween Caster) (fate)|]] is given as a reward to players for completing the event.

title: chaldea_summer_memory
body:
[b]Drifting Pioneer Diary: Blue Sky Land[br]Summer! Ocean! Pioneering! FGO Summer 2016 Chaldea Summer Memory ~The White Beach of Relaxation~[/b]
[quote]A Rayshift mishap leaves you adrift on an uninhabited island.
Nothing but the azure waves, the gentle breeze, and... some very sliceable crabs?
What began as escape boat construction becomes a pioneering expedition under Scáthach's command.
Can you make this island life a comfortable one?
And what happened to escaping?[/quote]

A limited-time [[Summer]] event in [[Fate/Grand Order]], released on the Japanese server on August 11, 2016 and on the NA server on July 26, 2018. title: suzume_no_oyado_no_katsudou_nisshi
body:
[b]Miyama Onsen Grand Shrine and Restaurant: Enma-tei[br]Sparrow's Inn Daily Report ~Records of the Enma-tei's Prosperity~[/b]
[quote]While Master was enjoying the bustling festivities of the New Year, an emergency call comes from the Command Room. The briefing this time details an all but harmless Singularity that appeared quite suddenly at a mountain hot springs resort. As such, the suggestion was to Rayshift there for a bit of rest and relaxation. Accompanied by the Servants who were drawn out by rumors of a hot springs trip, Master eagerly Rayshifts!

...But for some reason, everyone finds themselves in a deep forest overrun by a band of mischievous monkeys. After they save a mysterious sparrow from the primates' attack, it invites them to a nearby hot springs inn as a demonstration of gratitude for their help.

The inn looks magnificent at first sight, but behind its grandiose exterior, something seems off...[/quote]

A limited time [[New Year]] event in [[Fate/Grand Order]], released on the Japanese server on January 1, 2019 and on the NA server on January 1, 2021.

title: saber_wars
body:
[b]SABER WARS ~The Caliburn Awakens~[br]Lily's Cosmic Winter Rebellion[/b]
[quote]It is a period of Holy Grail War. CHALDEA enjoys an uneasy moment of peace as the struggle for humanity's future continues. Seeking the elusive ARTORIUM, a mysterious alien has appeared from the sky, but her true motives remain hidden. Saber Lily, the youngest fighter of the Unenhanced NP Alliance, sets out on a journey that will shape her destiny...
[/quote]
A limited time event in [[Fate/Grand Order]], released on the Japanese server on January 20, 2016 and on the NA server on January 4, 2018. It introduces the concept of the [[Servant Universe (fate)|]] and heavily parodies [[Star Wars]]. [[Saber Lily]] (originally only available as pre-registration bonus) is given to players as a reward for completing the event.

title: setsubun_shuen_emaki
body:
[b]The Tale of Setsubun: Oni Pagoda Festival[/b]
[quote]This story happens sometime...somewhere. A minute story is discovered in the remote countryside of Japan.
There, a mysterious tower has been raised in a place where no building should stand. The structure's height and shape are architecturally impossible, and its purpose and function are unclear.
What manner of secrets could this tower hold?

And as for the two horned beings who were seen Rayshifting around the time the minute Singularity was detected...
What could they be scheming?
[/quote]

A limited time [[Setsubun]]-themed event in [[Fate/Grand Order]], released on the Japanese server on January 24, 2018 and on the NA server on January 27, 2020.

title: london_(fate/grand_order)
body:
[b]Fourth Singularity: The Mist City, London[/b]
[quote]
The fourth Grand Order is set in 1888.

The Great British Empire in the Industrial Revolution Age where civilization flourished.

This new fierce battle shall commence around the fourth Holy Grail, in this city isolated by a demonic fog.
[/quote]
The fourth singularity in [[Fate/Grand Order]]. It's set in the year 1888 in the city of [[London]] during the industrial revolution, where the city has been enveloped in a magical [[fog]] created by a steam engine powered by the era's [[holy grail (fate)|]].

title: solomon_(singularity)_(fate/grand_order)
body:
[b]Final Singularity: The Grand Temple of Time, Solomon[/b]
[quote]
With the seven Singularities repaired, the final battleground awaits in a Singularity that exists outside human history.
Your foes: the 72 Demon Gods who protect the throne of the Mage King Solomon.
The ultimate battle for humanity's future is about to begin!
[/quote]
The final singularity in [[Fate/Grand Order]]. Set in the year 2016 in [[Grand Caster (fate)|Solomon]]'s [[Ars Paulina (fate)|temple]], it serves as a grand finale to the first arc, with the [[absolutely everyone|majority of servants]] joining in the fight.

Released on the Japanese server on December 22, 2016 and on the NA server on December 20, 2018. It was adapted into a movie by [[Cloverworks]], [i]Fate/Grand Order: Final Singularity - The Grand Temple of Time: Solomon[/i].

title: shimousa_(fate/grand_order)
body:
[b][s]Pseudo-Singularity III[/s] Pseudo-Parallel World: The Stage of Carnage, Shimousa[/b]
[quote]
Miyamoto Musashi...a strange woman encountered in the minute Singularity.
The concept of Pruning Theoretical Phenomenon...and a being who continuously warps from one world to another...

Too much remains a mystery about this woman.
Historically, Miyamoto Musashi was a man who made his mark on the world as a master swordsman.
What reason could there be for these two who share a name to be split as they are?

A new story unfolds after Musashi reappears and reunites with everyone at Chaldea.
The time has come for the Seven Duels of Swordmasters to begin.
[/quote]
The third "pseudo-singularity" in [[Fate/Grand Order]], set in the historical region of Shimousa in [[Japan]] in the year 1639 (or Kan'ei 16). It's later determined that rather than being a pseudo-singularity, it's actually a parallel world [spoiler]similar to a Lostbelt set up by [[Ashiya Douman (fate)|]] and the Alien God.[/spoiler] Unlike other singularities, Ritsuka arrives in Shimousa through dreaming instead of by rayshifting.

Released on the Japanese server on October 14, 2017 and on the NA server on October 10, 2019. It was adapted into a manga by [[Wataru Rei]].

Upon release of Shimousa (and the other pseudo-singularities), the true name of several new servants was initially hidden; however official Fate/Grand Order media would later forego keeping their true names hidden in promotional materials. Their aliases are listed below, but their true names are used on Danbooru for tagging.

title: heian-kyou_(fate/grand_order)
body:
[b]Naraka Mandala, Heian-kyou[/b]
[quote]
The members of Chaldea return from their brutal struggle in the Fifth Lostbelt. As they prepare to begin their mission in the next Lostbelt, they detect a new Singularity, which is marked as a sign of Humanity's collapse. Until now, it had been believed that no such signs could be seen upon the bleached earth, where human history has come to an end.

It is in the Heian period in Japan. The splendid capital Heian-kyou enjoys tremendous prosperity under the enduring rule of the Fujiwara clan.

But after Rayshifting to what should be a time of plenty, Chaldea instead finds a world overrun by evil spirits and infested by horrid abominations. In this land, "Imperial Warriors" conduct a ritual modeled after a Holy Grail War.

Who are the Imperial Warriors, and what purpose does their ritual serve? In this mysterious, millennium-old city, Chaldea's Master faces the machinations of the Beautiful Carnivore.
[/quote]
A singularity that formed on the bleached earth in [[Fate/Grand Order]], created and maintained by [[Ashiya Douman (fate)|]] where he attempts to transition it into its own Lostbelt. It's set in Japan in A.D. 1008 and takes place following the events of [[Olympus (fate/grand order)|]]. Released on the Japanese server December 4, 2020 and on the NA server on November 21, 2022.

The [[Tamamo Nine]] were a group of nine [[fox girl]] servants first debuted in [[Fate/Extra]]. They were created after the goddess [[Amaterasu (fate)|]] cut off her nine tails which later gained consciousness of their own.

title: dr._hiluluk
body:
A supporting character from the backstory of the manga and anime [[One Piece]]. He became the foster father and mentor of [[Tony Tony Chopper]] and inspired him to become a doctor and his life goal of finding a cure for all known diseases.

Sadly, [spoiler]he died from ingesting an explosive potion right in front of [[Wapol|his country's tyrannical ruler]], although he was as good as dead due to a relapse of a fatal disease and having drunk a soup Chopper unwittingly made from a terribly poisonous mushroom, but chose to go out on his own terms[/spoiler].

title: straitjacket
body:
A jacket worn to restrain or prevent movement of the arms.

Famously worn by the illusionist Harry Houdini in some of his escape tricks. Also commonly associated with mental hospitals around the turn of the 20th century, when they were commonly used to restrain violent patients.

title: guitar
body:
A plucked stringed [[instrument]], either [[electric guitar|electric]] or [[acoustic guitar|acoustic]], with a long neck.

Closely related to the [[bass guitar]] except that a standard guitar typically has [b]six strings[/b] and six tuning pegs at the top of the neck. On rare occasions a guitar may have more strings than that (e.g. 12).

Do not tag [[bass guitar]]s as regular guitars. A bass guitar has four strings, while a regular guitar has six.

h4. Examples

* !post #7621630: [[Acoustic guitar]]
* !post #8105640: Semihollow [[electric guitar]]

title: urban_legend
body:
A modern form of folklore, consisting of fictitious stories, often believed to be true, passed around by word of mouth, chain letters or emails, or websites such as [[futaba channel|2chan]]. These stories are set in our contemporary world and frequently describe unexplainable or unusual events, reflect broad societal fears around e.g. crime and sex, and often feature a twist ending.

title: dooby
body:
A English-speaking [[indie virtual youtuber|Indie]] [[virtual youtuber|VTuber]]. Lore-wise, she is a [[mouse girl|jerboa girl]].

She has [[short hair|short]] [[blonde hair]] with a [[black hair|black]] [[streaked hair|streaks]]. Her eyes are also [[green eyes|green]]. She has a [[mouse tail|jerboa tail]].

Her default costume is a [[train conductor]] outfit in which she wears a [[blue hat]], a [[blue jacket]] over [[blue overalls]] and a [[white shirt]] with [[white gloves]], [[white socks]] and [[blue shoes]].

title: vickers_machine_gun
body:
The Vickers machine gun was an extremely-successful development of the [[Maxim gun]] design for the [[British army]], and was used from [[World War I]] until the late 1960s on land, sea, and air. It can be visually distinguished from the base Maxim gun and other derivative designs by its ridged water shroud around the barrel, and by the large muzzle booster. 

Vickers guns were commonly mounted on [[tripod]]s for use on land, while aircraft guns had a perforated barrel shroud to turn it into an air-cooled gun. Vickers guns were commonly used as hull machine guns for British tanks during [[World War II]], and Vickers guns of larger calibers even served as [[anti-aircraft gun]]s on British warships into the early Second World War. 

The Vickers was finally officially retired from the British Army in 1968, replaced by the [[FN MAG]].

h4. See also

* [[MG08]] The German version of the Maxim gun. 
* [[PM1910]] The Russian version of the Maxim gun. 

h4. External links

* "Wikipedia: Vickers machine gun":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vickers_machine_gun]

title: midjourney
body:
A generative artificial intelligence program and service created and operated by the self-named independent research organization based in San Francisco. Midjourney, like OpenAI's [[DALL-E]] and Stability AI's [[Stable Diffusion]], generates images from natural language descriptions called "prompts".

As with any [[AI-generated]] tools, Midjourney-created images were forbidden, unless the image was sufficiently altered enough from the original to be qualified as [[AI-assisted]] (such as using it simply for the background image).

title: hela_(marvel)
body:
Hela is a fictional supervillain appearing in American comic books published by [[Marvel|Marvel Comics]]. Created by writer [[Stan Lee]] and artist Jack Kirby, Hela first appeared in [i]Journey into Mystery[/i] #102 (Mar. 1964) and is based on the goddess [[Hel (norse mythology)|]] from [[Norse Mythology]].

The Asgardian goddess of death who serves as the ruler of Hel and Niflheim, she is usually depicted as an adversary to [[Thor (marvel)|]]. Hela was originally a Black Infinity Stone created by the then All-Father [[Bor Burison]]. They were suddenly attack by [[Thanos]] from the future and as the stone transformed into a [[baby]] girl, Thanos tried to sacrifice her in order to gain her powers but was ultimately defeated. She was later put in the care of [[Loki (marvel)|]] and Angrboda, raising her as their daughter. In the [[Marvel]] cinematic universe, she is the eldest daughter of [[Odin (marvel)|]], making her [[Thor (marvel)|]] and [[Loki (marvel)|]]'s older sister. 

As an Asgardian woman and the Goddess of Death, Hela possesses several powers, including Asgardian Physiology (superhuman strength, speed, stamina, durability), immortality, magic manipulation and control over life and death. Hela has [[long hair|long]] [[black hair]], [[green eyes]] and usually wears a [[black bodysuit|black]] and [[green bodysuit]], a [[green cloak]] and a [[cowl]] with a spiked [[crown]]. Without her cloak, she becomes very weak and her powers are greatly reduced.

Hela made her live-action debut in the [[Marvel]] film [[Thor: Ragnarok]], where she is portrayed by Catherine Blanchett. She has also appeared in various other Marvel-releated media like TV shows and video games, including [[Marvel Future Fight]] and [[Marvel Rivals]].

title: pm1910
body:
The Russian derivative of the [[Maxim gun]] design, the PM Model 1910 was a heavy [[machine gun]] adopted by the [[Imperial Russian Army]] in 1910, that saw extensive use from [[World War I]] to the [[Russian Civil War]], [[World War II]], and even continues to see use in the [[Russo-Ukrainian War]] in modern times. 

The weapon is visually distinguished by its ridged water jacket that has a large flat cap on top, for filling the jacket from the top. It is typically depicted mounted in a two-wheeled cart with a large shield to protect the gunner and loader. 

h4. See also

* [[MG08]] The German version of the Maxim gun. 
* [[Vickers machine gun]] The British version of the Maxim gun. 

h4. External links

* "Wikipedia: PM M1910":[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/PM_M1910]
